86/*
87 * CHV supports eDP 1.4 that have more link rates.
88 * Below only provides the fixed rate but exclude variable rate.
89 */
90static const struct dp_link_dpll chv_dpll[] = {
91 /*
92 * CHV requires to program fractional division for m2.
93 * m2 is stored in fixed point format using formula below
94 * (m2_int << 22) | m2_fraction
95 */
96 { 162000, /* m2_int = 32, m2_fraction = 1677722 */
97 { .p1 = 4, .p2 = 2, .n = 1, .m1 = 2, .m2 = 0x819999a } },
98 { 270000, /* m2_int = 27, m2_fraction = 0 */
99 { .p1 = 4, .p2 = 1, .n = 1, .m1 = 2, .m2 = 0x6c00000 } },
100 { 540000, /* m2_int = 27, m2_fraction = 0 */
101 { .p1 = 2, .p2 = 1, .n = 1, .m1 = 2, .m2 = 0x6c00000 } }
102};

110/**
111 * is_edp - is the given port attached to an eDP panel (either CPU or PCH)
112 * @intel_dp: DP struct
113 *
114 * If a CPU or PCH DP output is attached to an eDP panel, this function
115 * will return true, and false otherwise.
116 */
117static bool is_edp(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
118{
119 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
120
121 return intel_dig_port->base.type == INTEL_OUTPUT_EDP;
122}

143static unsigned int intel_dp_unused_lane_mask(int lane_count)
144{
145 return ~((1 << lane_count) - 1) & 0xf;
146}

148static int
149intel_dp_max_link_bw(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
150{
151 int max_link_bw = intel_dp->dpcd[DP_MAX_LINK_RATE];
152
153 switch (max_link_bw) {
154 case DP_LINK_BW_1_62:
155 case DP_LINK_BW_2_7:
156 case DP_LINK_BW_5_4:
157 break;
158 default:
159 WARN(1, "invalid max DP link bw val %x, using 1.62Gbps\n",
160 max_link_bw);
161 max_link_bw = DP_LINK_BW_1_62;
162 break;
163 }
164 return max_link_bw;
165}
166
167static u8 intel_dp_max_lane_count(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
168{
169 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
170 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dig_port->base.base.dev;
171 u8 source_max, sink_max;
172
173 source_max = 4;
174 if (HAS_DDI(dev) && intel_dig_port->port == PORT_A &&
175 (intel_dig_port->saved_port_bits & DDI_A_4_LANES) == 0)
176 source_max = 2;
177
178 sink_max = drm_dp_max_lane_count(intel_dp->dpcd);
179
180 return min(source_max, sink_max);
181}
182
183/*
184 * The units on the numbers in the next two are... bizarre. Examples will
185 * make it clearer; this one parallels an example in the eDP spec.
186 *
187 * intel_dp_max_data_rate for one lane of 2.7GHz evaluates as:
188 *
189 * 270000 * 1 * 8 / 10 == 216000
190 *
191 * The actual data capacity of that configuration is 2.16Gbit/s, so the
192 * units are decakilobits. ->clock in a drm_display_mode is in kilohertz -
193 * or equivalently, kilopixels per second - so for 1680x1050R it'd be
194 * 119000. At 18bpp that's 2142000 kilobits per second.
195 *
196 * Thus the strange-looking division by 10 in intel_dp_link_required, to
197 * get the result in decakilobits instead of kilobits.
198 */
199
200static int
201intel_dp_link_required(int pixel_clock, int bpp)
202{
203 return (pixel_clock * bpp + 9) / 10;
204}
205
206static int
207intel_dp_max_data_rate(int max_link_clock, int max_lanes)
208{
209 return (max_link_clock * max_lanes * 8) / 10;
210}

212static enum drm_mode_status
213intel_dp_mode_valid(struct drm_connector *connector,
214 struct drm_display_mode *mode)
215{
216 struct intel_dp *intel_dp = intel_attached_dp(connector);
217 struct intel_connector *intel_connector = to_intel_connector(connector);
218 struct drm_display_mode *fixed_mode = intel_connector->panel.fixed_mode;
219 int target_clock = mode->clock;
220 int max_rate, mode_rate, max_lanes, max_link_clock;
221
222 if (is_edp(intel_dp) && fixed_mode) {
223 if (mode->hdisplay > fixed_mode->hdisplay)
224 return MODE_PANEL;
225
226 if (mode->vdisplay > fixed_mode->vdisplay)
227 return MODE_PANEL;
228
229 target_clock = fixed_mode->clock;
230 }
231
232 max_link_clock = intel_dp_max_link_rate(intel_dp);
233 max_lanes = intel_dp_max_lane_count(intel_dp);
234
235 max_rate = intel_dp_max_data_rate(max_link_clock, max_lanes);
236 mode_rate = intel_dp_link_required(target_clock, 18);
237
238 if (mode_rate > max_rate)
239 return MODE_CLOCK_HIGH;
240
241 if (mode->clock < 10000)
242 return MODE_CLOCK_LOW;
243
244 if (mode->flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_DBLCLK)
245 return MODE_H_ILLEGAL;
246
247 return MODE_OK;
248}

250uint32_t intel_dp_pack_aux(const uint8_t *src, int src_bytes)
251{
252 int i;
253 uint32_t v = 0;
254
255 if (src_bytes > 4)
256 src_bytes = 4;
257 for (i = 0; i < src_bytes; i++)
258 v |= ((uint32_t) src[i]) << ((3-i) * 8);
259 return v;
260}
261
262static void intel_dp_unpack_aux(uint32_t src, uint8_t *dst, int dst_bytes)
263{
264 int i;
265 if (dst_bytes > 4)
266 dst_bytes = 4;
267 for (i = 0; i < dst_bytes; i++)
268 dst[i] = src >> ((3-i) * 8);
269}

278static void pps_lock(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
279{
280 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
281 struct intel_encoder *encoder = &intel_dig_port->base;
282 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->base.dev;
283 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
284 enum intel_display_power_domain power_domain;
285
286 /*
287 * See vlv_power_sequencer_reset() why we need
288 * a power domain reference here.
289 */
290 power_domain = intel_display_port_aux_power_domain(encoder);
291 intel_display_power_get(dev_priv, power_domain);
292
293 mutex_lock(&dev_priv->pps_mutex);
294}
295
296static void pps_unlock(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
297{
298 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
299 struct intel_encoder *encoder = &intel_dig_port->base;
300 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->base.dev;
301 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
302 enum intel_display_power_domain power_domain;
303
304 mutex_unlock(&dev_priv->pps_mutex);
305
306 power_domain = intel_display_port_aux_power_domain(encoder);
307 intel_display_power_put(dev_priv, power_domain);
308}

310static void
311vlv_power_sequencer_kick(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
312{
313 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
314 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dig_port->base.base.dev;
315 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
316 enum i915_pipe pipe = intel_dp->pps_pipe;
317 bool pll_enabled, release_cl_override = false;
318 enum dpio_phy phy = DPIO_PHY(pipe);
319 enum dpio_channel ch = vlv_pipe_to_channel(pipe);
320 uint32_t DP;
321
322 if (WARN(I915_READ(intel_dp->output_reg) & DP_PORT_EN,
323 "skipping pipe %c power seqeuncer kick due to port %c being active\n",
324 pipe_name(pipe), port_name(intel_dig_port->port)))
325 return;
326
327 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("kicking pipe %c power sequencer for port %c\n",
328 pipe_name(pipe), port_name(intel_dig_port->port));
329
330 /* Preserve the BIOS-computed detected bit. This is
331 * supposed to be read-only.
332 */
333 DP = I915_READ(intel_dp->output_reg) & DP_DETECTED;
334 DP |= DP_VOLTAGE_0_4 | DP_PRE_EMPHASIS_0;
335 DP |= DP_PORT_WIDTH(1);
336 DP |= DP_LINK_TRAIN_PAT_1;
337
338 if (IS_CHERRYVIEW(dev))
339 DP |= DP_PIPE_SELECT_CHV(pipe);
340 else if (pipe == PIPE_B)
341 DP |= DP_PIPEB_SELECT;
342
343 pll_enabled = I915_READ(DPLL(pipe)) & DPLL_VCO_ENABLE;
344
345 /*
346 * The DPLL for the pipe must be enabled for this to work.
347 * So enable temporarily it if it's not already enabled.
348 */
349 if (!pll_enabled) {
350 release_cl_override = IS_CHERRYVIEW(dev) &&
351 !chv_phy_powergate_ch(dev_priv, phy, ch, true);
352
353 vlv_force_pll_on(dev, pipe, IS_CHERRYVIEW(dev) ?
354 &chv_dpll[0].dpll : &vlv_dpll[0].dpll);
355 }
356
357 /*
358 * Similar magic as in intel_dp_enable_port().
359 * We _must_ do this port enable + disable trick
360 * to make this power seqeuencer lock onto the port.
361 * Otherwise even VDD force bit won't work.
362 */
363 I915_WRITE(intel_dp->output_reg, DP);
364 POSTING_READ(intel_dp->output_reg);
365
366 I915_WRITE(intel_dp->output_reg, DP | DP_PORT_EN);
367 POSTING_READ(intel_dp->output_reg);
368
369 I915_WRITE(intel_dp->output_reg, DP & ~DP_PORT_EN);
370 POSTING_READ(intel_dp->output_reg);
371
372 if (!pll_enabled) {
373 vlv_force_pll_off(dev, pipe);
374
375 if (release_cl_override)
376 chv_phy_powergate_ch(dev_priv, phy, ch, false);
377 }
378}

380static enum i915_pipe
381vlv_power_sequencer_pipe(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
382{
383 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
384 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dig_port->base.base.dev;
385 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv __lockdep_used = dev->dev_private;
386 struct intel_encoder *encoder;
387 unsigned int pipes = (1 << PIPE_A) | (1 << PIPE_B);
388 enum i915_pipe pipe;
389
390 lockdep_assert_held(&dev_priv->pps_mutex);
391
392 /* We should never land here with regular DP ports */
393 WARN_ON(!is_edp(intel_dp));
394
395 if (intel_dp->pps_pipe != INVALID_PIPE)
396 return intel_dp->pps_pipe;
397
398 /*
399 * We don't have power sequencer currently.
400 * Pick one that's not used by other ports.
401 */
402 list_for_each_entry(encoder, &dev->mode_config.encoder_list,
403 base.head) {
404 struct intel_dp *tmp;
405
406 if (encoder->type != INTEL_OUTPUT_EDP)
407 continue;
408
409 tmp = enc_to_intel_dp(&encoder->base);
410
411 if (tmp->pps_pipe != INVALID_PIPE)
412 pipes &= ~(1 << tmp->pps_pipe);
413 }
414
415 /*
416 * Didn't find one. This should not happen since there
417 * are two power sequencers and up to two eDP ports.
418 */
419 if (WARN_ON(pipes == 0))
420 pipe = PIPE_A;
421 else
422 pipe = ffs(pipes) - 1;
423
424 vlv_steal_power_sequencer(dev, pipe);
425 intel_dp->pps_pipe = pipe;
426
427 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("picked pipe %c power sequencer for port %c\n",
428 pipe_name(intel_dp->pps_pipe),
429 port_name(intel_dig_port->port));
430
431 /* init power sequencer on this pipe and port */
432 intel_dp_init_panel_power_sequencer(dev, intel_dp);
433 intel_dp_init_panel_power_sequencer_registers(dev, intel_dp);
434
435 /*
436 * Even vdd force doesn't work until we've made
437 * the power sequencer lock in on the port.
438 */
439 vlv_power_sequencer_kick(intel_dp);
440
441 return intel_dp->pps_pipe;
442}

459static bool vlv_pipe_any(struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv,

461{
462 return true;

464
465static enum i915_pipe
466vlv_initial_pps_pipe(struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv,
467 enum port port,
468 vlv_pipe_check pipe_check)
469{
470 enum i915_pipe pipe;
471
472 for (pipe = PIPE_A; pipe <= PIPE_B; pipe++) {
473 u32 port_sel = I915_READ(VLV_PIPE_PP_ON_DELAYS(pipe)) &
474 PANEL_PORT_SELECT_MASK;
475
476 if (port_sel != PANEL_PORT_SELECT_VLV(port))
477 continue;
478
479 if (!pipe_check(dev_priv, pipe))
480 continue;
481
482 return pipe;
483 }
484
485 return INVALID_PIPE;
486}

488static void
489vlv_initial_power_sequencer_setup(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
490{
491 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
492 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dig_port->base.base.dev;
493 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
494 enum port port = intel_dig_port->port;
495
496 lockdep_assert_held(&dev_priv->pps_mutex);
497
498 /* try to find a pipe with this port selected */
499 /* first pick one where the panel is on */
500 intel_dp->pps_pipe = vlv_initial_pps_pipe(dev_priv, port,
501 vlv_pipe_has_pp_on);
502 /* didn't find one? pick one where vdd is on */
503 if (intel_dp->pps_pipe == INVALID_PIPE)
504 intel_dp->pps_pipe = vlv_initial_pps_pipe(dev_priv, port,
505 vlv_pipe_has_vdd_on);
506 /* didn't find one? pick one with just the correct port */
507 if (intel_dp->pps_pipe == INVALID_PIPE)
508 intel_dp->pps_pipe = vlv_initial_pps_pipe(dev_priv, port,
509 vlv_pipe_any);
510
511 /* didn't find one? just let vlv_power_sequencer_pipe() pick one when needed */
512 if (intel_dp->pps_pipe == INVALID_PIPE) {
513 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("no initial power sequencer for port %c\n",
514 port_name(port));
515 return;
516 }
517
518 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("initial power sequencer for port %c: pipe %c\n",
519 port_name(port), pipe_name(intel_dp->pps_pipe));
520
521 intel_dp_init_panel_power_sequencer(dev, intel_dp);
522 intel_dp_init_panel_power_sequencer_registers(dev, intel_dp);
523}
524
525void vlv_power_sequencer_reset(struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv)
526{
527 struct drm_device *dev = dev_priv->dev;
528 struct intel_encoder *encoder;
529
530 if (WARN_ON(!IS_VALLEYVIEW(dev)))
531 return;
532
533 /*
534 * We can't grab pps_mutex here due to deadlock with power_domain
535 * mutex when power_domain functions are called while holding pps_mutex.
536 * That also means that in order to use pps_pipe the code needs to
537 * hold both a power domain reference and pps_mutex, and the power domain
538 * reference get/put must be done while _not_ holding pps_mutex.
539 * pps_{lock,unlock}() do these steps in the correct order, so one
540 * should use them always.
541 */
542
543 list_for_each_entry(encoder, &dev->mode_config.encoder_list, base.head) {
544 struct intel_dp *intel_dp;
545
546 if (encoder->type != INTEL_OUTPUT_EDP)
547 continue;
548
549 intel_dp = enc_to_intel_dp(&encoder->base);
550 intel_dp->pps_pipe = INVALID_PIPE;
551 }
552}

554static u32 _pp_ctrl_reg(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
555{
556 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dp_to_dev(intel_dp);
557
558 if (IS_BROXTON(dev))
559 return BXT_PP_CONTROL(0);
560 else if (HAS_PCH_SPLIT(dev))
561 return PCH_PP_CONTROL;
562 else
563 return VLV_PIPE_PP_CONTROL(vlv_power_sequencer_pipe(intel_dp));
564}
565
566static u32 _pp_stat_reg(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
567{
568 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dp_to_dev(intel_dp);
569
570 if (IS_BROXTON(dev))
571 return BXT_PP_STATUS(0);
572 else if (HAS_PCH_SPLIT(dev))
573 return PCH_PP_STATUS;
574 else
575 return VLV_PIPE_PP_STATUS(vlv_power_sequencer_pipe(intel_dp));
576}

578/* Reboot notifier handler to shutdown panel power to guarantee T12 timing
579 This function only applicable when panel PM state is not to be tracked */
580static int edp_notify_handler(struct notifier_block *this, unsigned long code,
581 void *unused)
582{
583 struct intel_dp *intel_dp = container_of(this, typeof(* intel_dp),
584 edp_notifier);
585 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dp_to_dev(intel_dp);
586 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
587
588 if (!is_edp(intel_dp) || code != SYS_RESTART)
589 return 0;
590
591 pps_lock(intel_dp);
592
593 if (IS_VALLEYVIEW(dev)) {
594 enum i915_pipe pipe = vlv_power_sequencer_pipe(intel_dp);
595 u32 pp_ctrl_reg, pp_div_reg;
596 u32 pp_div;
597
598 pp_ctrl_reg = VLV_PIPE_PP_CONTROL(pipe);
599 pp_div_reg = VLV_PIPE_PP_DIVISOR(pipe);
600 pp_div = I915_READ(pp_div_reg);
601 pp_div &= PP_REFERENCE_DIVIDER_MASK;
602
603 /* 0x1F write to PP_DIV_REG sets max cycle delay */
604 I915_WRITE(pp_div_reg, pp_div | 0x1F);
605 I915_WRITE(pp_ctrl_reg, PANEL_UNLOCK_REGS | PANEL_POWER_OFF);
606 msleep(intel_dp->panel_power_cycle_delay);
607 }
608
609 pps_unlock(intel_dp);
610
611 return 0;
612}

614static bool edp_have_panel_power(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
615{
616 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dp_to_dev(intel_dp);
617 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
618
619 lockdep_assert_held(&dev_priv->pps_mutex);
620
621 if (IS_VALLEYVIEW(dev) &&
622 intel_dp->pps_pipe == INVALID_PIPE)
623 return false;
624
625 return (I915_READ(_pp_stat_reg(intel_dp)) & PP_ON) != 0;
626}
627
628static bool edp_have_panel_vdd(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
629{
630 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dp_to_dev(intel_dp);
631 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
632
633 lockdep_assert_held(&dev_priv->pps_mutex);
634
635 if (IS_VALLEYVIEW(dev) &&
636 intel_dp->pps_pipe == INVALID_PIPE)
637 return false;
638
639 return I915_READ(_pp_ctrl_reg(intel_dp)) & EDP_FORCE_VDD;
640}
641
642static void
643intel_dp_check_edp(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
644{
645 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dp_to_dev(intel_dp);
646 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
647
648 if (!is_edp(intel_dp))
649 return;
650
651 if (!edp_have_panel_power(intel_dp) && !edp_have_panel_vdd(intel_dp)) {
652 WARN(1, "eDP powered off while attempting aux channel communication.\n");
653 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Status 0x%08x Control 0x%08x\n",
654 I915_READ(_pp_stat_reg(intel_dp)),
655 I915_READ(_pp_ctrl_reg(intel_dp)));
656 }
657}
658
659static uint32_t
660intel_dp_aux_wait_done(struct intel_dp *intel_dp, bool has_aux_irq)
661{
662 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
663 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dig_port->base.base.dev;
664 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
665 uint32_t ch_ctl = intel_dp->aux_ch_ctl_reg;
666 uint32_t status;
667 bool done;
668
669#define C (((status = I915_READ_NOTRACE(ch_ctl)) & DP_AUX_CH_CTL_SEND_BUSY) == 0)
670#ifdef __NetBSD__
671 if (has_aux_irq && !cold) {
672 int ret;
673 spin_lock(&dev_priv->gmbus_wait_lock);
674 DRM_SPIN_TIMED_WAIT_NOINTR_UNTIL(ret,
675 &dev_priv->gmbus_wait_queue, &dev_priv->gmbus_wait_lock,
676 msecs_to_jiffies_timeout(10),
677 C);
678 if (ret < 0) /* Failure: pretend same as done. */
679 done = true;
680 else if (ret == 0) /* Timed out: not done. */
681 done = false;
682 else /* Succeeded (ret > 0): done. */
683 done = true;
684 spin_unlock(&dev_priv->gmbus_wait_lock);
685 } else {
686 done = wait_for_atomic(C, 10) == 0;
687 }
688#else
689 if (has_aux_irq)
690 done = wait_event_timeout(dev_priv->gmbus_wait_queue, C,
691 msecs_to_jiffies_timeout(10));
692 else
693 done = wait_for_atomic(C, 10) == 0;
694#endif
695 if (!done)
696 DRM_ERROR("dp aux hw did not signal timeout (has irq: %i)!\n",
697 has_aux_irq);
698#undef C
699
700 return status;
701}

703static uint32_t i9xx_get_aux_clock_divider(struct intel_dp *intel_dp, int index)
704{
705 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
706 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dig_port->base.base.dev;
707
708 /*
709 * The clock divider is based off the hrawclk, and would like to run at
710 * 2MHz. So, take the hrawclk value and divide by 2 and use that
711 */
712 return index ? 0 : intel_hrawclk(dev) / 2;
713}
714
715static uint32_t ilk_get_aux_clock_divider(struct intel_dp *intel_dp, int index)
716{
717 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
718 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dig_port->base.base.dev;
719 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
720
721 if (index)
722 return 0;
723
724 if (intel_dig_port->port == PORT_A) {
725 return DIV_ROUND_UP(dev_priv->cdclk_freq, 2000);
726
727 } else {
728 return DIV_ROUND_UP(intel_pch_rawclk(dev), 2);
729 }
730}
731
732static uint32_t hsw_get_aux_clock_divider(struct intel_dp *intel_dp, int index)
733{
734 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
735 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dig_port->base.base.dev;
736 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
737
738 if (intel_dig_port->port == PORT_A) {
739 if (index)
740 return 0;
741 return DIV_ROUND_CLOSEST(dev_priv->cdclk_freq, 2000);
742 } else if (dev_priv->pch_id == INTEL_PCH_LPT_DEVICE_ID_TYPE) {
743 /* Workaround for non-ULT HSW */
744 switch (index) {
745 case 0: return 63;
746 case 1: return 72;
747 default: return 0;
748 }
749 } else {
750 return index ? 0 : DIV_ROUND_UP(intel_pch_rawclk(dev), 2);
751 }
752}
753
754static uint32_t vlv_get_aux_clock_divider(struct intel_dp *intel_dp, int index)
755{
756 return index ? 0 : 100;
757}
758
759static uint32_t skl_get_aux_clock_divider(struct intel_dp *intel_dp, int index)
760{
761 /*
762 * SKL doesn't need us to program the AUX clock divider (Hardware will
763 * derive the clock from CDCLK automatically). We still implement the
764 * get_aux_clock_divider vfunc to plug-in into the existing code.
765 */
766 return index ? 0 : 1;
767}
768
769static uint32_t i9xx_get_aux_send_ctl(struct intel_dp *intel_dp,
770 bool has_aux_irq,
771 int send_bytes,
772 uint32_t aux_clock_divider)
773{
774 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
775 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dig_port->base.base.dev;
776 uint32_t precharge, timeout;
777
778 if (IS_GEN6(dev))
779 precharge = 3;
780 else
781 precharge = 5;
782
783 if (IS_BROADWELL(dev) && intel_dp->aux_ch_ctl_reg == DPA_AUX_CH_CTL)
784 timeout = DP_AUX_CH_CTL_TIME_OUT_600us;
785 else
786 timeout = DP_AUX_CH_CTL_TIME_OUT_400us;
787
788 return DP_AUX_CH_CTL_SEND_BUSY |
789 DP_AUX_CH_CTL_DONE |
790 (has_aux_irq ? DP_AUX_CH_CTL_INTERRUPT : 0) |
791 DP_AUX_CH_CTL_TIME_OUT_ERROR |
792 timeout |
793 DP_AUX_CH_CTL_RECEIVE_ERROR |
794 (send_bytes << DP_AUX_CH_CTL_MESSAGE_SIZE_SHIFT) |
795 (precharge << DP_AUX_CH_CTL_PRECHARGE_2US_SHIFT) |
796 (aux_clock_divider << DP_AUX_CH_CTL_BIT_CLOCK_2X_SHIFT);
797}
798
799static uint32_t skl_get_aux_send_ctl(struct intel_dp *intel_dp,
800 bool has_aux_irq,
801 int send_bytes,
802 uint32_t unused)
803{
804 return DP_AUX_CH_CTL_SEND_BUSY |
805 DP_AUX_CH_CTL_DONE |
806 (has_aux_irq ? DP_AUX_CH_CTL_INTERRUPT : 0) |
807 DP_AUX_CH_CTL_TIME_OUT_ERROR |
808 DP_AUX_CH_CTL_TIME_OUT_1600us |
809 DP_AUX_CH_CTL_RECEIVE_ERROR |
810 (send_bytes << DP_AUX_CH_CTL_MESSAGE_SIZE_SHIFT) |
811 DP_AUX_CH_CTL_SYNC_PULSE_SKL(32);
812}
813
814static int
815intel_dp_aux_ch(struct intel_dp *intel_dp,
816 const uint8_t *send, int send_bytes,
817 uint8_t *recv, int recv_size)
818{
819 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
820 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dig_port->base.base.dev;
821 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
822 uint32_t ch_ctl = intel_dp->aux_ch_ctl_reg;
823 uint32_t ch_data = ch_ctl + 4;
824 uint32_t aux_clock_divider;
825 int i, ret, recv_bytes;
826 uint32_t status;
827 int try, clock = 0;
828 bool has_aux_irq = HAS_AUX_IRQ(dev);
829 bool vdd;
830
831 pps_lock(intel_dp);
832
833 /*
834 * We will be called with VDD already enabled for dpcd/edid/oui reads.
835 * In such cases we want to leave VDD enabled and it's up to upper layers
836 * to turn it off. But for eg. i2c-dev access we need to turn it on/off
837 * ourselves.
838 */
839 vdd = edp_panel_vdd_on(intel_dp);
840
841 /* dp aux is extremely sensitive to irq latency, hence request the
842 * lowest possible wakeup latency and so prevent the cpu from going into
843 * deep sleep states.
844 */
845 pm_qos_update_request(&dev_priv->pm_qos, 0);
846
847 intel_dp_check_edp(intel_dp);
848
849 /* Try to wait for any previous AUX channel activity */
850 for (try = 0; try < 3; try++) {
851 status = I915_READ_NOTRACE(ch_ctl);
852 if ((status & DP_AUX_CH_CTL_SEND_BUSY) == 0)
853 break;
854 msleep(1);
855 }
856
857 if (try == 3) {
858 static u32 last_status = -1;
859 const u32 status = I915_READ(ch_ctl);
860
861 if (status != last_status) {
862 WARN(1, "dp_aux_ch not started status 0x%08x\n",
863 status);
864 last_status = status;
865 }
866
867 ret = -EBUSY;
868 goto out;
869 }
870
871 /* Only 5 data registers! */
872 if (WARN_ON(send_bytes > 20 || recv_size > 20)) {
873 ret = -E2BIG;
874 goto out;
875 }
876
877 while ((aux_clock_divider = intel_dp->get_aux_clock_divider(intel_dp, clock++))) {
878 u32 send_ctl = intel_dp->get_aux_send_ctl(intel_dp,
879 has_aux_irq,
880 send_bytes,
881 aux_clock_divider);
882
883 /* Must try at least 3 times according to DP spec */
884 for (try = 0; try < 5; try++) {
885 /* Load the send data into the aux channel data registers */
886 for (i = 0; i < send_bytes; i += 4)
887 I915_WRITE(ch_data + i,
888 intel_dp_pack_aux(send + i,
889 send_bytes - i));
890
891 /* Send the command and wait for it to complete */
892 I915_WRITE(ch_ctl, send_ctl);
893
894 status = intel_dp_aux_wait_done(intel_dp, has_aux_irq);
895
896 /* Clear done status and any errors */
897 I915_WRITE(ch_ctl,
898 status |
899 DP_AUX_CH_CTL_DONE |
900 DP_AUX_CH_CTL_TIME_OUT_ERROR |
901 DP_AUX_CH_CTL_RECEIVE_ERROR);
902
903 if (status & DP_AUX_CH_CTL_TIME_OUT_ERROR)
904 continue;
905
906 /* DP CTS 1.2 Core Rev 1.1, 4.2.1.1 & 4.2.1.2
907 * 400us delay required for errors and timeouts
908 * Timeout errors from the HW already meet this
909 * requirement so skip to next iteration
910 */
911 if (status & DP_AUX_CH_CTL_RECEIVE_ERROR) {
912 usleep_range(400, 500);
913 continue;
914 }
915 if (status & DP_AUX_CH_CTL_DONE)
916 goto done;
917 }
918 }
919
920 if ((status & DP_AUX_CH_CTL_DONE) == 0) {
921 DRM_ERROR("dp_aux_ch not done status 0x%08x\n", status);
922 ret = -EBUSY;
923 goto out;
924 }
925
926done:
927 /* Check for timeout or receive error.
928 * Timeouts occur when the sink is not connected
929 */
930 if (status & DP_AUX_CH_CTL_RECEIVE_ERROR) {
931 DRM_ERROR("dp_aux_ch receive error status 0x%08x\n", status);
932 ret = -EIO;
933 goto out;
934 }
935
936 /* Timeouts occur when the device isn't connected, so they're
937 * "normal" -- don't fill the kernel log with these */
938 if (status & DP_AUX_CH_CTL_TIME_OUT_ERROR) {
939 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("dp_aux_ch timeout status 0x%08x\n", status);
940 ret = -ETIMEDOUT;
941 goto out;
942 }
943
944 /* Unload any bytes sent back from the other side */
945 recv_bytes = ((status & DP_AUX_CH_CTL_MESSAGE_SIZE_MASK) >>
946 DP_AUX_CH_CTL_MESSAGE_SIZE_SHIFT);
947 if (recv_bytes > recv_size)
948 recv_bytes = recv_size;
949
950 for (i = 0; i < recv_bytes; i += 4)
951 intel_dp_unpack_aux(I915_READ(ch_data + i),
952 recv + i, recv_bytes - i);
953
954 ret = recv_bytes;
955out:
956 pm_qos_update_request(&dev_priv->pm_qos, PM_QOS_DEFAULT_VALUE);
957
958 if (vdd)
959 edp_panel_vdd_off(intel_dp, false);
960
961 pps_unlock(intel_dp);
962
963 return ret;
964}
965
966#define BARE_ADDRESS_SIZE 3
967#define HEADER_SIZE (BARE_ADDRESS_SIZE + 1)
968static ssize_t
969intel_dp_aux_transfer(struct drm_dp_aux *aux, struct drm_dp_aux_msg *msg)
970{
971 struct intel_dp *intel_dp = container_of(aux, struct intel_dp, aux);
972 uint8_t txbuf[20], rxbuf[20];
973 size_t txsize, rxsize;
974 int ret;
975
976 txbuf[0] = (msg->request << 4) |
977 ((msg->address >> 16) & 0xf);
978 txbuf[1] = (msg->address >> 8) & 0xff;
979 txbuf[2] = msg->address & 0xff;
980 txbuf[3] = msg->size - 1;
981
982 switch (msg->request & ~DP_AUX_I2C_MOT) {
983 case DP_AUX_NATIVE_WRITE:
984 case DP_AUX_I2C_WRITE:
985 case DP_AUX_I2C_WRITE_STATUS_UPDATE:
986 txsize = msg->size ? HEADER_SIZE + msg->size : BARE_ADDRESS_SIZE;
987 rxsize = 2; /* 0 or 1 data bytes */
988
989 if (WARN_ON(txsize > 20))
990 return -E2BIG;
991
992 memcpy(txbuf + HEADER_SIZE, msg->buffer, msg->size);
993
994 ret = intel_dp_aux_ch(intel_dp, txbuf, txsize, rxbuf, rxsize);
995 if (ret > 0) {
996 msg->reply = rxbuf[0] >> 4;
997
998 if (ret > 1) {
999 /* Number of bytes written in a short write. */
1000 ret = clamp_t(int, rxbuf[1], 0, msg->size);
1001 } else {
1002 /* Return payload size. */
1003 ret = msg->size;
1004 }
1005 }
1006 break;
1007
1008 case DP_AUX_NATIVE_READ:
1009 case DP_AUX_I2C_READ:
1010 txsize = msg->size ? HEADER_SIZE : BARE_ADDRESS_SIZE;
1011 rxsize = msg->size + 1;
1012
1013 if (WARN_ON(rxsize > 20))
1014 return -E2BIG;
1015
1016 ret = intel_dp_aux_ch(intel_dp, txbuf, txsize, rxbuf, rxsize);
1017 if (ret > 0) {
1018 msg->reply = rxbuf[0] >> 4;
1019 /*
1020 * Assume happy day, and copy the data. The caller is
1021 * expected to check msg->reply before touching it.
1022 *
1023 * Return payload size.
1024 */
1025 ret--;
1026 memcpy(msg->buffer, rxbuf + 1, ret);
1027 }
1028 break;
1029
1030 default:
1031 ret = -EINVAL;
1032 break;
1033 }
1034
1035 return ret;
1036}
1037
1038static void
1039intel_dp_aux_init(struct intel_dp *intel_dp, struct intel_connector *connector)
1040{
1041 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dp_to_dev(intel_dp);
1042 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
1043 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
1044 enum port port = intel_dig_port->port;
1045 struct ddi_vbt_port_info *info = &dev_priv->vbt.ddi_port_info[port];
1046 const char *name = NULL;
1047 uint32_t porte_aux_ctl_reg = DPA_AUX_CH_CTL;
1048 int ret;
1049
1050 /* On SKL we don't have Aux for port E so we rely on VBT to set
1051 * a proper alternate aux channel.
1052 */
1053 if ((IS_SKYLAKE(dev) || IS_KABYLAKE(dev)) && port == PORT_E) {
1054 switch (info->alternate_aux_channel) {
1055 case DP_AUX_B:
1056 porte_aux_ctl_reg = DPB_AUX_CH_CTL;
1057 break;
1058 case DP_AUX_C:
1059 porte_aux_ctl_reg = DPC_AUX_CH_CTL;
1060 break;
1061 case DP_AUX_D:
1062 porte_aux_ctl_reg = DPD_AUX_CH_CTL;
1063 break;
1064 case DP_AUX_A:
1065 default:
1066 porte_aux_ctl_reg = DPA_AUX_CH_CTL;
1067 }
1068 }
1069
1070 switch (port) {
1071 case PORT_A:
1072 intel_dp->aux_ch_ctl_reg = DPA_AUX_CH_CTL;
1073 name = "DPDDC-A";
1074 break;
1075 case PORT_B:
1076 intel_dp->aux_ch_ctl_reg = PCH_DPB_AUX_CH_CTL;
1077 name = "DPDDC-B";
1078 break;
1079 case PORT_C:
1080 intel_dp->aux_ch_ctl_reg = PCH_DPC_AUX_CH_CTL;
1081 name = "DPDDC-C";
1082 break;
1083 case PORT_D:
1084 intel_dp->aux_ch_ctl_reg = PCH_DPD_AUX_CH_CTL;
1085 name = "DPDDC-D";
1086 break;
1087 case PORT_E:
1088 intel_dp->aux_ch_ctl_reg = porte_aux_ctl_reg;
1089 name = "DPDDC-E";
1090 break;
1091 default:
1092 BUG();
1093 }
1094
1095 /*
1096 * The AUX_CTL register is usually DP_CTL + 0x10.
1097 *
1098 * On Haswell and Broadwell though:
1099 * - Both port A DDI_BUF_CTL and DDI_AUX_CTL are on the CPU
1100 * - Port B/C/D AUX channels are on the PCH, DDI_BUF_CTL on the CPU
1101 *
1102 * Skylake moves AUX_CTL back next to DDI_BUF_CTL, on the CPU.
1103 */
1104 if (!IS_HASWELL(dev) && !IS_BROADWELL(dev) && port != PORT_E)
1105 intel_dp->aux_ch_ctl_reg = intel_dp->output_reg + 0x10;
1106
1107 intel_dp->aux.name = name;
1108 intel_dp->aux.dev = dev->dev;
1109 intel_dp->aux.transfer = intel_dp_aux_transfer;
1110
1111#ifdef __NetBSD__
1112 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("registering %s bus for %s\n", name,
1113 device_xname(connector->base.dev->dev));
1114#else
1115 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("registering %s bus for %s\n", name,
1116 connector->base.kdev->kobj.name);
1117#endif
1118
1119 ret = drm_dp_aux_register(&intel_dp->aux);
1120 if (ret < 0) {
1121 DRM_ERROR("drm_dp_aux_register() for %s failed (%d)\n",
1122 name, ret);
1123 return;
1124 }
1125
1126#ifndef __NetBSD__
1127 ret = sysfs_create_link(&connector->base.kdev->kobj,
1128 &intel_dp->aux.ddc.dev.kobj,
1129 intel_dp->aux.ddc.dev.kobj.name);
1130 if (ret < 0) {
1131 DRM_ERROR("sysfs_create_link() for %s failed (%d)\n", name, ret);
1132 drm_dp_aux_unregister(&intel_dp->aux);
1133 }
1134#endif
1135}

1140#ifndef __NetBSD__
1141 struct intel_dp *intel_dp = intel_attached_dp(&intel_connector->base);

1152static void
1153skl_edp_set_pll_config(struct intel_crtc_state *pipe_config)
1154{
1155 u32 ctrl1;
1156
1157 memset(&pipe_config->dpll_hw_state, 0,
1158 sizeof(pipe_config->dpll_hw_state));
1159
1160 pipe_config->ddi_pll_sel = SKL_DPLL0;
1161 pipe_config->dpll_hw_state.cfgcr1 = 0;
1162 pipe_config->dpll_hw_state.cfgcr2 = 0;
1163
1164 ctrl1 = DPLL_CTRL1_OVERRIDE(SKL_DPLL0);
1165 switch (pipe_config->port_clock / 2) {
1166 case 81000:
1167 ctrl1 |= DPLL_CTRL1_LINK_RATE(DPLL_CTRL1_LINK_RATE_810,
1168 SKL_DPLL0);
1169 break;
1170 case 135000:
1171 ctrl1 |= DPLL_CTRL1_LINK_RATE(DPLL_CTRL1_LINK_RATE_1350,
1172 SKL_DPLL0);
1173 break;
1174 case 270000:
1175 ctrl1 |= DPLL_CTRL1_LINK_RATE(DPLL_CTRL1_LINK_RATE_2700,
1176 SKL_DPLL0);
1177 break;
1178 case 162000:
1179 ctrl1 |= DPLL_CTRL1_LINK_RATE(DPLL_CTRL1_LINK_RATE_1620,
1180 SKL_DPLL0);
1181 break;
1182 /* TBD: For DP link rates 2.16 GHz and 4.32 GHz, VCO is 8640 which
1183 results in CDCLK change. Need to handle the change of CDCLK by
1184 disabling pipes and re-enabling them */
1185 case 108000:
1186 ctrl1 |= DPLL_CTRL1_LINK_RATE(DPLL_CTRL1_LINK_RATE_1080,
1187 SKL_DPLL0);
1188 break;
1189 case 216000:
1190 ctrl1 |= DPLL_CTRL1_LINK_RATE(DPLL_CTRL1_LINK_RATE_2160,
1191 SKL_DPLL0);
1192 break;
1193
1194 }
1195 pipe_config->dpll_hw_state.ctrl1 = ctrl1;
1196}

1230static bool intel_dp_source_supports_hbr2(struct drm_device *dev)
1231{
1232 /* WaDisableHBR2:skl */
1233 if (IS_SKYLAKE(dev) && INTEL_REVID(dev) <= SKL_REVID_B0)
1234 return false;
1235
1236 if ((IS_HASWELL(dev) && !IS_HSW_ULX(dev)) || IS_BROADWELL(dev) ||
1237 (INTEL_INFO(dev)->gen >= 9))
1238 return true;
1239 else
1240 return false;
1241}
1242
1243static int
1244intel_dp_source_rates(struct drm_device *dev, const int **source_rates)
1245{
1246 int size;
1247
1248 if (IS_BROXTON(dev)) {
1249 *source_rates = bxt_rates;
1250 size = ARRAY_SIZE(bxt_rates);
1251 } else if (IS_SKYLAKE(dev) || IS_KABYLAKE(dev)) {
1252 *source_rates = skl_rates;
1253 size = ARRAY_SIZE(skl_rates);
1254 } else {
1255 *source_rates = default_rates;
1256 size = ARRAY_SIZE(default_rates);
1257 }
1258
1259 /* This depends on the fact that 5.4 is last value in the array */
1260 if (!intel_dp_source_supports_hbr2(dev))
1261 size--;
1262
1263 return size;
1264}

1266static void
1267intel_dp_set_clock(struct intel_encoder *encoder,
1268 struct intel_crtc_state *pipe_config)
1269{
1270 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->base.dev;
1271 const struct dp_link_dpll *divisor = NULL;
1272 int i, count = 0;
1273
1274 if (IS_G4X(dev)) {
1275 divisor = gen4_dpll;
1276 count = ARRAY_SIZE(gen4_dpll);
1277 } else if (HAS_PCH_SPLIT(dev)) {
1278 divisor = pch_dpll;
1279 count = ARRAY_SIZE(pch_dpll);
1280 } else if (IS_CHERRYVIEW(dev)) {
1281 divisor = chv_dpll;
1282 count = ARRAY_SIZE(chv_dpll);
1283 } else if (IS_VALLEYVIEW(dev)) {
1284 divisor = vlv_dpll;
1285 count = ARRAY_SIZE(vlv_dpll);
1286 }
1287
1288 if (divisor && count) {
1289 for (i = 0; i < count; i++) {
1290 if (pipe_config->port_clock == divisor[i].clock) {
1291 pipe_config->dpll = divisor[i].dpll;
1292 pipe_config->clock_set = true;
1293 break;
1294 }
1295 }
1296 }
1297}
1298
1299static int intersect_rates(const int *source_rates, int source_len,
1300 const int *sink_rates, int sink_len,
1301 int *common_rates)
1302{
1303 int i = 0, j = 0, k = 0;
1304
1305 while (i < source_len && j < sink_len) {
1306 if (source_rates[i] == sink_rates[j]) {
1307 if (WARN_ON(k >= DP_MAX_SUPPORTED_RATES))
1308 return k;
1309 common_rates[k] = source_rates[i];
1310 ++k;
1311 ++i;
1312 ++j;
1313 } else if (source_rates[i] < sink_rates[j]) {
1314 ++i;
1315 } else {
1316 ++j;
1317 }
1318 }
1319 return k;
1320}
1321
1322static int intel_dp_common_rates(struct intel_dp *intel_dp,
1323 int *common_rates)
1324{
1325 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dp_to_dev(intel_dp);
1326 const int *source_rates, *sink_rates;
1327 int source_len, sink_len;
1328
1329 sink_len = intel_dp_sink_rates(intel_dp, &sink_rates);
1330 source_len = intel_dp_source_rates(dev, &source_rates);
1331
1332 return intersect_rates(source_rates, source_len,
1333 sink_rates, sink_len,
1334 common_rates);
1335}
1336
1337static void snprintf_int_array(char *str, size_t len,
1338 const int *array, int nelem)
1339{
1340 int i;
1341
1342 str[0] = '\0';
1343
1344 for (i = 0; i < nelem; i++) {
1345 int r = snprintf(str, len, "%s%d", i ? ", " : "", array[i]);
1346 if (r >= len)
1347 return;
1348 str += r;
1349 len -= r;
1350 }
1351}
1352
1353static void intel_dp_print_rates(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
1354{
1355 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dp_to_dev(intel_dp);
1356 const int *source_rates, *sink_rates;
1357 int source_len, sink_len, common_len;
1358 int common_rates[DP_MAX_SUPPORTED_RATES];
1359 char str[128]; /* FIXME: too big for stack? */
1360
1361 if ((drm_debug & DRM_UT_KMS) == 0)
1362 return;
1363
1364 source_len = intel_dp_source_rates(dev, &source_rates);
1365 snprintf_int_array(str, sizeof(str), source_rates, source_len);
1366 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("source rates: %s\n", str);
1367
1368 sink_len = intel_dp_sink_rates(intel_dp, &sink_rates);
1369 snprintf_int_array(str, sizeof(str), sink_rates, sink_len);
1370 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("sink rates: %s\n", str);
1371
1372 common_len = intel_dp_common_rates(intel_dp, common_rates);
1373 snprintf_int_array(str, sizeof(str), common_rates, common_len);
1374 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("common rates: %s\n", str);
1375}

1377static int rate_to_index(int find, const int *rates)
1378{
1379 int i = 0;
1380
1381 for (i = 0; i < DP_MAX_SUPPORTED_RATES; ++i)
1382 if (find == rates[i])
1383 break;
1384
1385 return i;
1386}
1387
1388int
1389intel_dp_max_link_rate(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
1390{
1391 int rates[DP_MAX_SUPPORTED_RATES] = {};
1392 int len;
1393
1394 len = intel_dp_common_rates(intel_dp, rates);
1395 if (WARN_ON(len <= 0))
1396 return 162000;
1397
1398 return rates[rate_to_index(0, rates) - 1];
1399}
1400
1401int intel_dp_rate_select(struct intel_dp *intel_dp, int rate)
1402{
1403 return rate_to_index(rate, intel_dp->sink_rates);
1404}

1406static void intel_dp_compute_rate(struct intel_dp *intel_dp, int port_clock,
1407 uint8_t *link_bw, uint8_t *rate_select)
1408{
1409 if (intel_dp->num_sink_rates) {
1410 *link_bw = 0;
1411 *rate_select =
1412 intel_dp_rate_select(intel_dp, port_clock);
1413 } else {
1414 *link_bw = drm_dp_link_rate_to_bw_code(port_clock);
1415 *rate_select = 0;
1416 }
1417}
1418
1419bool
1420intel_dp_compute_config(struct intel_encoder *encoder,
1421 struct intel_crtc_state *pipe_config)
1422{
1423 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->base.dev;
1424 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
1425 struct drm_display_mode *adjusted_mode = &pipe_config->base.adjusted_mode;
1426 struct intel_dp *intel_dp = enc_to_intel_dp(&encoder->base);
1427 enum port port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp)->port;
1428 struct intel_crtc *intel_crtc = to_intel_crtc(pipe_config->base.crtc);
1429 struct intel_connector *intel_connector = intel_dp->attached_connector;
1430 int lane_count, clock;
1431 int min_lane_count = 1;
1432 int max_lane_count = intel_dp_max_lane_count(intel_dp);
1433 /* Conveniently, the link BW constants become indices with a shift...*/
1434 int min_clock = 0;
1435 int max_clock;
1436 int bpp, mode_rate;
1437 int link_avail, link_clock;
1438 int common_rates[DP_MAX_SUPPORTED_RATES] = {};
1439 int common_len;
1440 uint8_t link_bw, rate_select;
1441
1442 common_len = intel_dp_common_rates(intel_dp, common_rates);
1443
1444 /* No common link rates between source and sink */
1445 WARN_ON(common_len <= 0);
1446
1447 max_clock = common_len - 1;
1448
1449 if (HAS_PCH_SPLIT(dev) && !HAS_DDI(dev) && port != PORT_A)
1450 pipe_config->has_pch_encoder = true;
1451
1452 pipe_config->has_dp_encoder = true;
1453 pipe_config->has_drrs = false;
1454 pipe_config->has_audio = intel_dp->has_audio && port != PORT_A;
1455
1456 if (is_edp(intel_dp) && intel_connector->panel.fixed_mode) {
1457 intel_fixed_panel_mode(intel_connector->panel.fixed_mode,
1458 adjusted_mode);
1459
1460 if (INTEL_INFO(dev)->gen >= 9) {
1461 int ret;
1462 ret = skl_update_scaler_crtc(pipe_config);
1463 if (ret)
1464 return ret;
1465 }
1466
1467 if (!HAS_PCH_SPLIT(dev))
1468 intel_gmch_panel_fitting(intel_crtc, pipe_config,
1469 intel_connector->panel.fitting_mode);
1470 else
1471 intel_pch_panel_fitting(intel_crtc, pipe_config,
1472 intel_connector->panel.fitting_mode);
1473 }
1474
1475 if (adjusted_mode->flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_DBLCLK)
1476 return false;
1477
1478 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("DP link computation with max lane count %i "
1479 "max bw %d pixel clock %iKHz\n",
1480 max_lane_count, common_rates[max_clock],
1481 adjusted_mode->crtc_clock);
1482
1483 /* Walk through all bpp values. Luckily they're all nicely spaced with 2
1484 * bpc in between. */
1485 bpp = pipe_config->pipe_bpp;
1486 if (is_edp(intel_dp)) {
1487
1488 /* Get bpp from vbt only for panels that dont have bpp in edid */
1489 if (intel_connector->base.display_info.bpc == 0 &&
1490 (dev_priv->vbt.edp_bpp && dev_priv->vbt.edp_bpp < bpp)) {
1491 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("clamping bpp for eDP panel to BIOS-provided %i\n",
1492 dev_priv->vbt.edp_bpp);
1493 bpp = dev_priv->vbt.edp_bpp;
1494 }
1495
1496 /*
1497 * Use the maximum clock and number of lanes the eDP panel
1498 * advertizes being capable of. The panels are generally
1499 * designed to support only a single clock and lane
1500 * configuration, and typically these values correspond to the
1501 * native resolution of the panel.
1502 */
1503 min_lane_count = max_lane_count;
1504 min_clock = max_clock;
1505 }
1506
1507 for (; bpp >= 6*3; bpp -= 2*3) {
1508 mode_rate = intel_dp_link_required(adjusted_mode->crtc_clock,
1509 bpp);
1510
1511 for (clock = min_clock; clock <= max_clock; clock++) {
1512 for (lane_count = min_lane_count;
1513 lane_count <= max_lane_count;
1514 lane_count <<= 1) {
1515
1516 link_clock = common_rates[clock];
1517 link_avail = intel_dp_max_data_rate(link_clock,
1518 lane_count);
1519
1520 if (mode_rate <= link_avail) {
1521 goto found;
1522 }
1523 }
1524 }
1525 }
1526
1527 return false;
1528
1529found:
1530 if (intel_dp->color_range_auto) {
1531 /*
1532 * See:
1533 * CEA-861-E - 5.1 Default Encoding Parameters
1534 * VESA DisplayPort Ver.1.2a - 5.1.1.1 Video Colorimetry
1535 */
1536 pipe_config->limited_color_range =
1537 bpp != 18 && drm_match_cea_mode(adjusted_mode) > 1;
1538 } else {
1539 pipe_config->limited_color_range =
1540 intel_dp->limited_color_range;
1541 }
1542
1543 pipe_config->lane_count = lane_count;
1544
1545 pipe_config->pipe_bpp = bpp;
1546 pipe_config->port_clock = common_rates[clock];
1547
1548 intel_dp_compute_rate(intel_dp, pipe_config->port_clock,
1549 &link_bw, &rate_select);
1550
1551 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("DP link bw %02x rate select %02x lane count %d clock %d bpp %d\n",
1552 link_bw, rate_select, pipe_config->lane_count,
1553 pipe_config->port_clock, bpp);
1554 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("DP link bw required %i available %i\n",
1555 mode_rate, link_avail);
1556
1557 intel_link_compute_m_n(bpp, lane_count,
1558 adjusted_mode->crtc_clock,
1559 pipe_config->port_clock,
1560 &pipe_config->dp_m_n);
1561
1562 if (intel_connector->panel.downclock_mode != NULL &&
1563 dev_priv->drrs.type == SEAMLESS_DRRS_SUPPORT) {
1564 pipe_config->has_drrs = true;
1565 intel_link_compute_m_n(bpp, lane_count,
1566 intel_connector->panel.downclock_mode->clock,
1567 pipe_config->port_clock,
1568 &pipe_config->dp_m2_n2);
1569 }
1570
1571 if ((IS_SKYLAKE(dev) || IS_KABYLAKE(dev)) && is_edp(intel_dp))
1572 skl_edp_set_pll_config(pipe_config);
1573 else if (IS_BROXTON(dev))
1574 /* handled in ddi */;
1575 else if (IS_HASWELL(dev) || IS_BROADWELL(dev))
1576 hsw_dp_set_ddi_pll_sel(pipe_config);
1577 else
1578 intel_dp_set_clock(encoder, pipe_config);
1579
1580 return true;
1581}
1582
1583static void ironlake_set_pll_cpu_edp(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
1584{
1585 struct intel_digital_port *dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
1586 struct intel_crtc *crtc = to_intel_crtc(dig_port->base.base.crtc);
1587 struct drm_device *dev = crtc->base.dev;
1588 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
1589 u32 dpa_ctl;
1590
1591 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("eDP PLL enable for clock %d\n",
1592 crtc->config->port_clock);
1593 dpa_ctl = I915_READ(DP_A);
1594 dpa_ctl &= ~DP_PLL_FREQ_MASK;
1595
1596 if (crtc->config->port_clock == 162000) {
1597 /* For a long time we've carried around a ILK-DevA w/a for the
1598 * 160MHz clock. If we're really unlucky, it's still required.
1599 */
1600 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("160MHz cpu eDP clock, might need ilk devA w/a\n");
1601 dpa_ctl |= DP_PLL_FREQ_160MHZ;
1602 intel_dp->DP |= DP_PLL_FREQ_160MHZ;
1603 } else {
1604 dpa_ctl |= DP_PLL_FREQ_270MHZ;
1605 intel_dp->DP |= DP_PLL_FREQ_270MHZ;
1606 }
1607
1608 I915_WRITE(DP_A, dpa_ctl);
1609
1610 POSTING_READ(DP_A);
1611 udelay(500);
1612}

1614void intel_dp_set_link_params(struct intel_dp *intel_dp,
1615 const struct intel_crtc_state *pipe_config)
1616{
1617 intel_dp->link_rate = pipe_config->port_clock;
1618 intel_dp->lane_count = pipe_config->lane_count;
1619}
1620
1621static void intel_dp_prepare(struct intel_encoder *encoder)
1622{
1623 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->base.dev;
1624 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
1625 struct intel_dp *intel_dp = enc_to_intel_dp(&encoder->base);
1626 enum port port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp)->port;
1627 struct intel_crtc *crtc = to_intel_crtc(encoder->base.crtc);
1628 const struct drm_display_mode *adjusted_mode = &crtc->config->base.adjusted_mode;
1629
1630 intel_dp_set_link_params(intel_dp, crtc->config);
1631
1632 /*
1633 * There are four kinds of DP registers:
1634 *
1635 * IBX PCH
1636 * SNB CPU
1637 * IVB CPU
1638 * CPT PCH
1639 *
1640 * IBX PCH and CPU are the same for almost everything,
1641 * except that the CPU DP PLL is configured in this
1642 * register
1643 *
1644 * CPT PCH is quite different, having many bits moved
1645 * to the TRANS_DP_CTL register instead. That
1646 * configuration happens (oddly) in ironlake_pch_enable
1647 */
1648
1649 /* Preserve the BIOS-computed detected bit. This is
1650 * supposed to be read-only.
1651 */
1652 intel_dp->DP = I915_READ(intel_dp->output_reg) & DP_DETECTED;
1653
1654 /* Handle DP bits in common between all three register formats */
1655 intel_dp->DP |= DP_VOLTAGE_0_4 | DP_PRE_EMPHASIS_0;
1656 intel_dp->DP |= DP_PORT_WIDTH(crtc->config->lane_count);
1657
1658 if (crtc->config->has_audio)
1659 intel_dp->DP |= DP_AUDIO_OUTPUT_ENABLE;
1660
1661 /* Split out the IBX/CPU vs CPT settings */
1662
1663 if (IS_GEN7(dev) && port == PORT_A) {
1664 if (adjusted_mode->flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_PHSYNC)
1665 intel_dp->DP |= DP_SYNC_HS_HIGH;
1666 if (adjusted_mode->flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_PVSYNC)
1667 intel_dp->DP |= DP_SYNC_VS_HIGH;
1668 intel_dp->DP |= DP_LINK_TRAIN_OFF_CPT;
1669
1670 if (drm_dp_enhanced_frame_cap(intel_dp->dpcd))
1671 intel_dp->DP |= DP_ENHANCED_FRAMING;
1672
1673 intel_dp->DP |= crtc->pipe << 29;
1674 } else if (HAS_PCH_CPT(dev) && port != PORT_A) {
1675 u32 trans_dp;
1676
1677 intel_dp->DP |= DP_LINK_TRAIN_OFF_CPT;
1678
1679 trans_dp = I915_READ(TRANS_DP_CTL(crtc->pipe));
1680 if (drm_dp_enhanced_frame_cap(intel_dp->dpcd))
1681 trans_dp |= TRANS_DP_ENH_FRAMING;
1682 else
1683 trans_dp &= ~TRANS_DP_ENH_FRAMING;
1684 I915_WRITE(TRANS_DP_CTL(crtc->pipe), trans_dp);
1685 } else {
1686 if (!HAS_PCH_SPLIT(dev) && !IS_VALLEYVIEW(dev) &&
1687 crtc->config->limited_color_range)
1688 intel_dp->DP |= DP_COLOR_RANGE_16_235;
1689
1690 if (adjusted_mode->flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_PHSYNC)
1691 intel_dp->DP |= DP_SYNC_HS_HIGH;
1692 if (adjusted_mode->flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_PVSYNC)
1693 intel_dp->DP |= DP_SYNC_VS_HIGH;
1694 intel_dp->DP |= DP_LINK_TRAIN_OFF;
1695
1696 if (drm_dp_enhanced_frame_cap(intel_dp->dpcd))
1697 intel_dp->DP |= DP_ENHANCED_FRAMING;
1698
1699 if (IS_CHERRYVIEW(dev))
1700 intel_dp->DP |= DP_PIPE_SELECT_CHV(crtc->pipe);
1701 else if (crtc->pipe == PIPE_B)
1702 intel_dp->DP |= DP_PIPEB_SELECT;
1703 }
1704}

1706#define IDLE_ON_MASK (PP_ON | PP_SEQUENCE_MASK | 0 | PP_SEQUENCE_STATE_MASK)
1707#define IDLE_ON_VALUE (PP_ON | PP_SEQUENCE_NONE | 0 | PP_SEQUENCE_STATE_ON_IDLE)
1708
1709#define IDLE_OFF_MASK (PP_ON | PP_SEQUENCE_MASK | 0 | 0)
1710#define IDLE_OFF_VALUE (0 | PP_SEQUENCE_NONE | 0 | 0)
1711
1712#define IDLE_CYCLE_MASK (PP_ON | PP_SEQUENCE_MASK | PP_CYCLE_DELAY_ACTIVE | PP_SEQUENCE_STATE_MASK)
1713#define IDLE_CYCLE_VALUE (0 | PP_SEQUENCE_NONE | 0 | PP_SEQUENCE_STATE_OFF_IDLE)
1714
1715static void wait_panel_status(struct intel_dp *intel_dp,
1716 u32 mask,
1717 u32 value)
1718{
1719 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dp_to_dev(intel_dp);
1720 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
1721 u32 pp_stat_reg, pp_ctrl_reg;
1722
1723 lockdep_assert_held(&dev_priv->pps_mutex);
1724
1725 pp_stat_reg = _pp_stat_reg(intel_dp);
1726 pp_ctrl_reg = _pp_ctrl_reg(intel_dp);
1727
1728 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("mask %08x value %08x status %08x control %08x\n",
1729 mask, value,
1730 I915_READ(pp_stat_reg),
1731 I915_READ(pp_ctrl_reg));
1732
1733 if (_wait_for((I915_READ(pp_stat_reg) & mask) == value, 5000, 10)) {
1734 DRM_ERROR("Panel status timeout: status %08x control %08x\n",
1735 I915_READ(pp_stat_reg),
1736 I915_READ(pp_ctrl_reg));
1737 }
1738
1739 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Wait complete\n");
1740}

1777
1778/* Read the current pp_control value, unlocking the register if it
1779 * is locked
1780 */
1781
1782static u32 ironlake_get_pp_control(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
1783{
1784 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dp_to_dev(intel_dp);
1785 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
1786 u32 control;
1787
1788 lockdep_assert_held(&dev_priv->pps_mutex);
1789
1790 control = I915_READ(_pp_ctrl_reg(intel_dp));
1791 if (!IS_BROXTON(dev)) {
1792 control &= ~PANEL_UNLOCK_MASK;
1793 control |= PANEL_UNLOCK_REGS;
1794 }
1795 return control;
1796}
1797
1798/*
1799 * Must be paired with edp_panel_vdd_off().
1800 * Must hold pps_mutex around the whole on/off sequence.
1801 * Can be nested with intel_edp_panel_vdd_{on,off}() calls.
1802 */
1803static bool edp_panel_vdd_on(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
1804{
1805 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dp_to_dev(intel_dp);
1806 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
1807 struct intel_encoder *intel_encoder = &intel_dig_port->base;
1808 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
1809 enum intel_display_power_domain power_domain;
1810 u32 pp;
1811 u32 pp_stat_reg, pp_ctrl_reg;
1812 bool need_to_disable = !intel_dp->want_panel_vdd;
1813
1814 lockdep_assert_held(&dev_priv->pps_mutex);
1815
1816 if (!is_edp(intel_dp))
1817 return false;
1818
1819 cancel_delayed_work(&intel_dp->panel_vdd_work);
1820 intel_dp->want_panel_vdd = true;
1821
1822 if (edp_have_panel_vdd(intel_dp))
1823 return need_to_disable;
1824
1825 power_domain = intel_display_port_aux_power_domain(intel_encoder);
1826 intel_display_power_get(dev_priv, power_domain);
1827
1828 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Turning eDP port %c VDD on\n",
1829 port_name(intel_dig_port->port));
1830
1831 if (!edp_have_panel_power(intel_dp))
1832 wait_panel_power_cycle(intel_dp);
1833
1834 pp = ironlake_get_pp_control(intel_dp);
1835 pp |= EDP_FORCE_VDD;
1836
1837 pp_stat_reg = _pp_stat_reg(intel_dp);
1838 pp_ctrl_reg = _pp_ctrl_reg(intel_dp);
1839
1840 I915_WRITE(pp_ctrl_reg, pp);
1841 POSTING_READ(pp_ctrl_reg);
1842 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("PP_STATUS: 0x%08x PP_CONTROL: 0x%08x\n",
1843 I915_READ(pp_stat_reg), I915_READ(pp_ctrl_reg));
1844 /*
1845 * If the panel wasn't on, delay before accessing aux channel
1846 */
1847 if (!edp_have_panel_power(intel_dp)) {
1848 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("eDP port %c panel power wasn't enabled\n",
1849 port_name(intel_dig_port->port));
1850 msleep(intel_dp->panel_power_up_delay);
1851 }
1852
1853 return need_to_disable;
1854}
1855
1856/*
1857 * Must be paired with intel_edp_panel_vdd_off() or
1858 * intel_edp_panel_off().
1859 * Nested calls to these functions are not allowed since
1860 * we drop the lock. Caller must use some higher level
1861 * locking to prevent nested calls from other threads.
1862 */
1863void intel_edp_panel_vdd_on(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
1864{
1865 bool vdd;
1866
1867 if (!is_edp(intel_dp))
1868 return;
1869
1870 pps_lock(intel_dp);
1871 vdd = edp_panel_vdd_on(intel_dp);
1872 pps_unlock(intel_dp);
1873
1874 I915_STATE_WARN(!vdd, "eDP port %c VDD already requested on\n",
1875 port_name(dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp)->port));
1876}
1877
1878static void edp_panel_vdd_off_sync(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
1879{
1880 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dp_to_dev(intel_dp);
1881 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
1882 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port =
1883 dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
1884 struct intel_encoder *intel_encoder = &intel_dig_port->base;
1885 enum intel_display_power_domain power_domain;
1886 u32 pp;
1887 u32 pp_stat_reg, pp_ctrl_reg;
1888
1889 lockdep_assert_held(&dev_priv->pps_mutex);
1890
1891 WARN_ON(intel_dp->want_panel_vdd);
1892
1893 if (!edp_have_panel_vdd(intel_dp))
1894 return;
1895
1896 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Turning eDP port %c VDD off\n",
1897 port_name(intel_dig_port->port));
1898
1899 pp = ironlake_get_pp_control(intel_dp);
1900 pp &= ~EDP_FORCE_VDD;
1901
1902 pp_ctrl_reg = _pp_ctrl_reg(intel_dp);
1903 pp_stat_reg = _pp_stat_reg(intel_dp);
1904
1905 I915_WRITE(pp_ctrl_reg, pp);
1906 POSTING_READ(pp_ctrl_reg);
1907
1908 /* Make sure sequencer is idle before allowing subsequent activity */
1909 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("PP_STATUS: 0x%08x PP_CONTROL: 0x%08x\n",
1910 I915_READ(pp_stat_reg), I915_READ(pp_ctrl_reg));
1911
1912 if ((pp & POWER_TARGET_ON) == 0)
1913 intel_dp->last_power_cycle = jiffies;
1914
1915 power_domain = intel_display_port_aux_power_domain(intel_encoder);
1916 intel_display_power_put(dev_priv, power_domain);
1917}
1918
1919static void edp_panel_vdd_work(struct work_struct *__work)
1920{
1921 struct intel_dp *intel_dp = container_of(to_delayed_work(__work),
1922 struct intel_dp, panel_vdd_work);
1923
1924 pps_lock(intel_dp);
1925 if (!intel_dp->want_panel_vdd)
1926 edp_panel_vdd_off_sync(intel_dp);
1927 pps_unlock(intel_dp);
1928}
1929
1930static void edp_panel_vdd_schedule_off(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
1931{
1932 unsigned long delay;
1933
1934 /*
1935 * Queue the timer to fire a long time from now (relative to the power
1936 * down delay) to keep the panel power up across a sequence of
1937 * operations.
1938 */
1939 delay = msecs_to_jiffies(intel_dp->panel_power_cycle_delay * 5);
1940 schedule_delayed_work(&intel_dp->panel_vdd_work, delay);
1941}
1942
1943/*
1944 * Must be paired with edp_panel_vdd_on().
1945 * Must hold pps_mutex around the whole on/off sequence.
1946 * Can be nested with intel_edp_panel_vdd_{on,off}() calls.
1947 */
1948static void edp_panel_vdd_off(struct intel_dp *intel_dp, bool sync)
1949{
1950 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv __lockdep_used =
1951 intel_dp_to_dev(intel_dp)->dev_private;
1952
1953 lockdep_assert_held(&dev_priv->pps_mutex);
1954
1955 if (!is_edp(intel_dp))
1956 return;
1957
1958 I915_STATE_WARN(!intel_dp->want_panel_vdd, "eDP port %c VDD not forced on",
1959 port_name(dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp)->port));
1960
1961 intel_dp->want_panel_vdd = false;
1962
1963 if (sync)
1964 edp_panel_vdd_off_sync(intel_dp);
1965 else
1966 edp_panel_vdd_schedule_off(intel_dp);
1967}
1968
1969static void edp_panel_on(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
1970{
1971 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dp_to_dev(intel_dp);
1972 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
1973 u32 pp;
1974 u32 pp_ctrl_reg;
1975
1976 lockdep_assert_held(&dev_priv->pps_mutex);
1977
1978 if (!is_edp(intel_dp))
1979 return;
1980
1981 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Turn eDP port %c panel power on\n",
1982 port_name(dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp)->port));
1983
1984 if (WARN(edp_have_panel_power(intel_dp),
1985 "eDP port %c panel power already on\n",
1986 port_name(dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp)->port)))
1987 return;
1988
1989 wait_panel_power_cycle(intel_dp);
1990
1991 pp_ctrl_reg = _pp_ctrl_reg(intel_dp);
1992 pp = ironlake_get_pp_control(intel_dp);
1993 if (IS_GEN5(dev)) {
1994 /* ILK workaround: disable reset around power sequence */
1995 pp &= ~PANEL_POWER_RESET;
1996 I915_WRITE(pp_ctrl_reg, pp);
1997 POSTING_READ(pp_ctrl_reg);
1998 }
1999
2000 pp |= POWER_TARGET_ON;
2001 if (!IS_GEN5(dev))
2002 pp |= PANEL_POWER_RESET;
2003
2004 I915_WRITE(pp_ctrl_reg, pp);
2005 POSTING_READ(pp_ctrl_reg);
2006
2007 wait_panel_on(intel_dp);
2008 intel_dp->last_power_on = jiffies;
2009
2010 if (IS_GEN5(dev)) {
2011 pp |= PANEL_POWER_RESET; /* restore panel reset bit */
2012 I915_WRITE(pp_ctrl_reg, pp);
2013 POSTING_READ(pp_ctrl_reg);
2014 }
2015}
2016
2017void intel_edp_panel_on(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
2018{
2019 if (!is_edp(intel_dp))
2020 return;
2021
2022 pps_lock(intel_dp);
2023 edp_panel_on(intel_dp);
2024 pps_unlock(intel_dp);
2025}

2027
2028static void edp_panel_off(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
2029{
2030 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
2031 struct intel_encoder *intel_encoder = &intel_dig_port->base;
2032 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dp_to_dev(intel_dp);
2033 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
2034 enum intel_display_power_domain power_domain;
2035 u32 pp;
2036 u32 pp_ctrl_reg;
2037
2038 lockdep_assert_held(&dev_priv->pps_mutex);
2039
2040 if (!is_edp(intel_dp))
2041 return;
2042
2043 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Turn eDP port %c panel power off\n",
2044 port_name(dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp)->port));
2045
2046 WARN(!intel_dp->want_panel_vdd, "Need eDP port %c VDD to turn off panel\n",
2047 port_name(dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp)->port));
2048
2049 pp = ironlake_get_pp_control(intel_dp);
2050 /* We need to switch off panel power _and_ force vdd, for otherwise some
2051 * panels get very unhappy and cease to work. */
2052 pp &= ~(POWER_TARGET_ON | PANEL_POWER_RESET | EDP_FORCE_VDD |
2053 EDP_BLC_ENABLE);
2054
2055 pp_ctrl_reg = _pp_ctrl_reg(intel_dp);
2056
2057 intel_dp->want_panel_vdd = false;
2058
2059 I915_WRITE(pp_ctrl_reg, pp);
2060 POSTING_READ(pp_ctrl_reg);
2061
2062 intel_dp->last_power_cycle = jiffies;
2063 wait_panel_off(intel_dp);
2064
2065 /* We got a reference when we enabled the VDD. */
2066 power_domain = intel_display_port_aux_power_domain(intel_encoder);
2067 intel_display_power_put(dev_priv, power_domain);
2068}

2070void intel_edp_panel_off(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
2071{
2072 if (!is_edp(intel_dp))
2073 return;
2074
2075 pps_lock(intel_dp);
2076 edp_panel_off(intel_dp);
2077 pps_unlock(intel_dp);
2078}

2080/* Enable backlight in the panel power control. */
2081static void _intel_edp_backlight_on(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
2082{
2083 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
2084 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dig_port->base.base.dev;
2085 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
2086 u32 pp;
2087 u32 pp_ctrl_reg;
2088

2091 * on, we may see slight flicker as the panel syncs with the eDP

2093 * allowing it to appear.

2095 wait_backlight_on(intel_dp);

2101
2102 pp_ctrl_reg = _pp_ctrl_reg(intel_dp);
2103
2104 I915_WRITE(pp_ctrl_reg, pp);
2105 POSTING_READ(pp_ctrl_reg);
2106
2107 pps_unlock(intel_dp);
2108}

2187static void ironlake_edp_pll_on(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
2188{
2189 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
2190 struct drm_crtc *crtc = intel_dig_port->base.base.crtc;
2191 struct drm_device *dev = crtc->dev;
2192 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
2193 u32 dpa_ctl;
2194
2195 assert_pipe_disabled(dev_priv,
2196 to_intel_crtc(crtc)->pipe);
2197
2198 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("\n");
2199 dpa_ctl = I915_READ(DP_A);
2200 WARN(dpa_ctl & DP_PLL_ENABLE, "dp pll on, should be off\n");
2201 WARN(dpa_ctl & DP_PORT_EN, "dp port still on, should be off\n");
2202
2203 /* We don't adjust intel_dp->DP while tearing down the link, to
2204 * facilitate link retraining (e.g. after hotplug). Hence clear all
2205 * enable bits here to ensure that we don't enable too much. */
2206 intel_dp->DP &= ~(DP_PORT_EN | DP_AUDIO_OUTPUT_ENABLE);
2207 intel_dp->DP |= DP_PLL_ENABLE;
2208 I915_WRITE(DP_A, intel_dp->DP);
2209 POSTING_READ(DP_A);
2210 udelay(200);
2211}
2212
2213static void ironlake_edp_pll_off(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
2214{
2215 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
2216 struct drm_crtc *crtc = intel_dig_port->base.base.crtc;
2217 struct drm_device *dev = crtc->dev;
2218 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
2219 u32 dpa_ctl;
2220
2221 assert_pipe_disabled(dev_priv,
2222 to_intel_crtc(crtc)->pipe);
2223
2224 dpa_ctl = I915_READ(DP_A);
2225 WARN((dpa_ctl & DP_PLL_ENABLE) == 0,
2226 "dp pll off, should be on\n");
2227 WARN(dpa_ctl & DP_PORT_EN, "dp port still on, should be off\n");
2228
2229 /* We can't rely on the value tracked for the DP register in
2230 * intel_dp->DP because link_down must not change that (otherwise link
2231 * re-training will fail. */
2232 dpa_ctl &= ~DP_PLL_ENABLE;
2233 I915_WRITE(DP_A, dpa_ctl);
2234 POSTING_READ(DP_A);
2235 udelay(200);
2236}
2237
2238/* If the sink supports it, try to set the power state appropriately */
2239void intel_dp_sink_dpms(struct intel_dp *intel_dp, int mode)
2240{
2241 int ret, i;
2242
2243 /* Should have a valid DPCD by this point */
2244 if (intel_dp->dpcd[DP_DPCD_REV] < 0x11)
2245 return;
2246
2247 if (mode != DRM_MODE_DPMS_ON) {
2248 ret = drm_dp_dpcd_writeb(&intel_dp->aux, DP_SET_POWER,
2249 DP_SET_POWER_D3);
2250 } else {
2251 /*
2252 * When turning on, we need to retry for 1ms to give the sink
2253 * time to wake up.
2254 */
2255 for (i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
2256 ret = drm_dp_dpcd_writeb(&intel_dp->aux, DP_SET_POWER,
2257 DP_SET_POWER_D0);
2258 if (ret == 1)
2259 break;
2260 msleep(1);
2261 }
2262 }
2263
2264 if (ret != 1)
2265 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("failed to %s sink power state\n",
2266 mode == DRM_MODE_DPMS_ON ? "enable" : "disable");
2267}
2268
2269static bool intel_dp_get_hw_state(struct intel_encoder *encoder,
2270 enum i915_pipe *pipe)
2271{
2272 struct intel_dp *intel_dp = enc_to_intel_dp(&encoder->base);
2273 enum port port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp)->port;
2274 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->base.dev;
2275 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
2276 enum intel_display_power_domain power_domain;
2277 u32 tmp;
2278
2279 power_domain = intel_display_port_power_domain(encoder);
2280 if (!intel_display_power_is_enabled(dev_priv, power_domain))
2281 return false;
2282
2283 tmp = I915_READ(intel_dp->output_reg);
2284
2285 if (!(tmp & DP_PORT_EN))
2286 return false;
2287
2288 if (IS_GEN7(dev) && port == PORT_A) {
2289 *pipe = PORT_TO_PIPE_CPT(tmp);
2290 } else if (HAS_PCH_CPT(dev) && port != PORT_A) {
2291 enum i915_pipe p;
2292
2293 for_each_pipe(dev_priv, p) {
2294 u32 trans_dp = I915_READ(TRANS_DP_CTL(p));
2295 if (TRANS_DP_PIPE_TO_PORT(trans_dp) == port) {
2296 *pipe = p;
2297 return true;
2298 }
2299 }
2300
2301 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("No pipe for dp port 0x%x found\n",
2302 intel_dp->output_reg);
2303 } else if (IS_CHERRYVIEW(dev)) {
2304 *pipe = DP_PORT_TO_PIPE_CHV(tmp);
2305 } else {
2306 *pipe = PORT_TO_PIPE(tmp);
2307 }
2308
2309 return true;
2310}
2311
2312static void intel_dp_get_config(struct intel_encoder *encoder,
2313 struct intel_crtc_state *pipe_config)
2314{
2315 struct intel_dp *intel_dp = enc_to_intel_dp(&encoder->base);
2316 u32 tmp, flags = 0;
2317 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->base.dev;
2318 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
2319 enum port port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp)->port;
2320 struct intel_crtc *crtc = to_intel_crtc(encoder->base.crtc);
2321 int dotclock;
2322
2323 tmp = I915_READ(intel_dp->output_reg);
2324
2325 pipe_config->has_audio = tmp & DP_AUDIO_OUTPUT_ENABLE && port != PORT_A;
2326
2327 if (HAS_PCH_CPT(dev) && port != PORT_A) {
2328 u32 trans_dp = I915_READ(TRANS_DP_CTL(crtc->pipe));
2329
2330 if (trans_dp & TRANS_DP_HSYNC_ACTIVE_HIGH)
2331 flags |= DRM_MODE_FLAG_PHSYNC;
2332 else
2333 flags |= DRM_MODE_FLAG_NHSYNC;
2334
2335 if (trans_dp & TRANS_DP_VSYNC_ACTIVE_HIGH)
2336 flags |= DRM_MODE_FLAG_PVSYNC;
2337 else
2338 flags |= DRM_MODE_FLAG_NVSYNC;
2339 } else {
2340 if (tmp & DP_SYNC_HS_HIGH)
2341 flags |= DRM_MODE_FLAG_PHSYNC;
2342 else
2343 flags |= DRM_MODE_FLAG_NHSYNC;
2344
2345 if (tmp & DP_SYNC_VS_HIGH)
2346 flags |= DRM_MODE_FLAG_PVSYNC;
2347 else
2348 flags |= DRM_MODE_FLAG_NVSYNC;
2349 }
2350
2351 pipe_config->base.adjusted_mode.flags |= flags;
2352
2353 if (!HAS_PCH_SPLIT(dev) && !IS_VALLEYVIEW(dev) &&
2354 tmp & DP_COLOR_RANGE_16_235)
2355 pipe_config->limited_color_range = true;
2356
2357 pipe_config->has_dp_encoder = true;
2358
2359 pipe_config->lane_count =
2360 ((tmp & DP_PORT_WIDTH_MASK) >> DP_PORT_WIDTH_SHIFT) + 1;
2361
2362 intel_dp_get_m_n(crtc, pipe_config);
2363
2364 if (port == PORT_A) {
2365 if ((I915_READ(DP_A) & DP_PLL_FREQ_MASK) == DP_PLL_FREQ_160MHZ)
2366 pipe_config->port_clock = 162000;
2367 else
2368 pipe_config->port_clock = 270000;
2369 }
2370
2371 dotclock = intel_dotclock_calculate(pipe_config->port_clock,
2372 &pipe_config->dp_m_n);
2373
2374 if (HAS_PCH_SPLIT(dev_priv->dev) && port != PORT_A)
2375 ironlake_check_encoder_dotclock(pipe_config, dotclock);
2376
2377 pipe_config->base.adjusted_mode.crtc_clock = dotclock;
2378
2379 if (is_edp(intel_dp) && dev_priv->vbt.edp_bpp &&
2380 pipe_config->pipe_bpp > dev_priv->vbt.edp_bpp) {
2381 /*
2382 * This is a big fat ugly hack.
2383 *
2384 * Some machines in UEFI boot mode provide us a VBT that has 18
2385 * bpp and 1.62 GHz link bandwidth for eDP, which for reasons
2386 * unknown we fail to light up. Yet the same BIOS boots up with
2387 * 24 bpp and 2.7 GHz link. Use the same bpp as the BIOS uses as
2388 * max, not what it tells us to use.
2389 *
2390 * Note: This will still be broken if the eDP panel is not lit
2391 * up by the BIOS, and thus we can't get the mode at module
2392 * load.
2393 */
2394 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("pipe has %d bpp for eDP panel, overriding BIOS-provided max %d bpp\n",
2395 pipe_config->pipe_bpp, dev_priv->vbt.edp_bpp);
2396 dev_priv->vbt.edp_bpp = pipe_config->pipe_bpp;
2397 }
2398}

2400static void intel_disable_dp(struct intel_encoder *encoder)
2401{
2402 struct intel_dp *intel_dp = enc_to_intel_dp(&encoder->base);
2403 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->base.dev;
2404 struct intel_crtc *crtc = to_intel_crtc(encoder->base.crtc);
2405
2406 if (crtc->config->has_audio)
2407 intel_audio_codec_disable(encoder);
2408
2409 if (HAS_PSR(dev) && !HAS_DDI(dev))
2410 intel_psr_disable(intel_dp);
2411
2412 /* Make sure the panel is off before trying to change the mode. But also
2413 * ensure that we have vdd while we switch off the panel. */
2414 intel_edp_panel_vdd_on(intel_dp);
2415 intel_edp_backlight_off(intel_dp);
2416 intel_dp_sink_dpms(intel_dp, DRM_MODE_DPMS_OFF);
2417 intel_edp_panel_off(intel_dp);
2418
2419 /* disable the port before the pipe on g4x */
2420 if (INTEL_INFO(dev)->gen < 5)
2421 intel_dp_link_down(intel_dp);
2422}

2440
2441static void chv_data_lane_soft_reset(struct intel_encoder *encoder,
2442 bool reset)
2443{
2444 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = to_i915(encoder->base.dev);
2445 enum dpio_channel ch = vlv_dport_to_channel(enc_to_dig_port(&encoder->base));
2446 struct intel_crtc *crtc = to_intel_crtc(encoder->base.crtc);
2447 enum i915_pipe pipe = crtc->pipe;
2448 uint32_t val;
2449
2450 val = vlv_dpio_read(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS01_DW0(ch));
2451 if (reset)
2452 val &= ~(DPIO_PCS_TX_LANE2_RESET | DPIO_PCS_TX_LANE1_RESET);
2453 else
2454 val |= DPIO_PCS_TX_LANE2_RESET | DPIO_PCS_TX_LANE1_RESET;
2455 vlv_dpio_write(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS01_DW0(ch), val);
2456
2457 if (crtc->config->lane_count > 2) {
2458 val = vlv_dpio_read(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS23_DW0(ch));
2459 if (reset)
2460 val &= ~(DPIO_PCS_TX_LANE2_RESET | DPIO_PCS_TX_LANE1_RESET);
2461 else
2462 val |= DPIO_PCS_TX_LANE2_RESET | DPIO_PCS_TX_LANE1_RESET;
2463 vlv_dpio_write(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS23_DW0(ch), val);
2464 }
2465
2466 val = vlv_dpio_read(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS01_DW1(ch));
2467 val |= CHV_PCS_REQ_SOFTRESET_EN;
2468 if (reset)
2469 val &= ~DPIO_PCS_CLK_SOFT_RESET;
2470 else
2471 val |= DPIO_PCS_CLK_SOFT_RESET;
2472 vlv_dpio_write(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS01_DW1(ch), val);
2473
2474 if (crtc->config->lane_count > 2) {
2475 val = vlv_dpio_read(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS23_DW1(ch));
2476 val |= CHV_PCS_REQ_SOFTRESET_EN;
2477 if (reset)
2478 val &= ~DPIO_PCS_CLK_SOFT_RESET;
2479 else
2480 val |= DPIO_PCS_CLK_SOFT_RESET;
2481 vlv_dpio_write(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS23_DW1(ch), val);
2482 }
2483}

2485static void chv_post_disable_dp(struct intel_encoder *encoder)
2486{
2487 struct intel_dp *intel_dp = enc_to_intel_dp(&encoder->base);
2488 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->base.dev;
2489 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
2490
2491 intel_dp_link_down(intel_dp);
2492
2493 mutex_lock(&dev_priv->sb_lock);
2494
2495 /* Assert data lane reset */

2497
2498 mutex_unlock(&dev_priv->sb_lock);
2499}
2500
2501static void
2502_intel_dp_set_link_train(struct intel_dp *intel_dp,
2503 uint32_t *DP,
2504 uint8_t dp_train_pat)
2505{
2506 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
2507 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dig_port->base.base.dev;
2508 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
2509 enum port port = intel_dig_port->port;
2510
2511 if (HAS_DDI(dev)) {
2512 uint32_t temp = I915_READ(DP_TP_CTL(port));
2513
2514 if (dp_train_pat & DP_LINK_SCRAMBLING_DISABLE)
2515 temp |= DP_TP_CTL_SCRAMBLE_DISABLE;
2516 else
2517 temp &= ~DP_TP_CTL_SCRAMBLE_DISABLE;
2518
2519 temp &= ~DP_TP_CTL_LINK_TRAIN_MASK;
2520 switch (dp_train_pat & DP_TRAINING_PATTERN_MASK) {
2521 case DP_TRAINING_PATTERN_DISABLE:
2522 temp |= DP_TP_CTL_LINK_TRAIN_NORMAL;
2523
2524 break;
2525 case DP_TRAINING_PATTERN_1:
2526 temp |= DP_TP_CTL_LINK_TRAIN_PAT1;
2527 break;
2528 case DP_TRAINING_PATTERN_2:
2529 temp |= DP_TP_CTL_LINK_TRAIN_PAT2;
2530 break;
2531 case DP_TRAINING_PATTERN_3:
2532 temp |= DP_TP_CTL_LINK_TRAIN_PAT3;
2533 break;
2534 }
2535 I915_WRITE(DP_TP_CTL(port), temp);
2536
2537 } else if ((IS_GEN7(dev) && port == PORT_A) ||
2538 (HAS_PCH_CPT(dev) && port != PORT_A)) {
2539 *DP &= ~DP_LINK_TRAIN_MASK_CPT;
2540
2541 switch (dp_train_pat & DP_TRAINING_PATTERN_MASK) {
2542 case DP_TRAINING_PATTERN_DISABLE:
2543 *DP |= DP_LINK_TRAIN_OFF_CPT;
2544 break;
2545 case DP_TRAINING_PATTERN_1:
2546 *DP |= DP_LINK_TRAIN_PAT_1_CPT;
2547 break;
2548 case DP_TRAINING_PATTERN_2:
2549 *DP |= DP_LINK_TRAIN_PAT_2_CPT;
2550 break;
2551 case DP_TRAINING_PATTERN_3:
2552 DRM_ERROR("DP training pattern 3 not supported\n");
2553 *DP |= DP_LINK_TRAIN_PAT_2_CPT;
2554 break;
2555 }
2556
2557 } else {
2558 if (IS_CHERRYVIEW(dev))
2559 *DP &= ~DP_LINK_TRAIN_MASK_CHV;
2560 else
2561 *DP &= ~DP_LINK_TRAIN_MASK;
2562
2563 switch (dp_train_pat & DP_TRAINING_PATTERN_MASK) {
2564 case DP_TRAINING_PATTERN_DISABLE:
2565 *DP |= DP_LINK_TRAIN_OFF;
2566 break;
2567 case DP_TRAINING_PATTERN_1:
2568 *DP |= DP_LINK_TRAIN_PAT_1;
2569 break;
2570 case DP_TRAINING_PATTERN_2:
2571 *DP |= DP_LINK_TRAIN_PAT_2;
2572 break;
2573 case DP_TRAINING_PATTERN_3:
2574 if (IS_CHERRYVIEW(dev)) {
2575 *DP |= DP_LINK_TRAIN_PAT_3_CHV;
2576 } else {
2577 DRM_ERROR("DP training pattern 3 not supported\n");
2578 *DP |= DP_LINK_TRAIN_PAT_2;
2579 }
2580 break;
2581 }
2582 }
2583}
2584
2585static void intel_dp_enable_port(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
2586{
2587 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dp_to_dev(intel_dp);
2588 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
2589
2590 /* enable with pattern 1 (as per spec) */
2591 _intel_dp_set_link_train(intel_dp, &intel_dp->DP,
2592 DP_TRAINING_PATTERN_1);
2593
2594 I915_WRITE(intel_dp->output_reg, intel_dp->DP);
2595 POSTING_READ(intel_dp->output_reg);
2596
2597 /*
2598 * Magic for VLV/CHV. We _must_ first set up the register
2599 * without actually enabling the port, and then do another
2600 * write to enable the port. Otherwise link training will
2601 * fail when the power sequencer is freshly used for this port.
2602 */
2603 intel_dp->DP |= DP_PORT_EN;
2604
2605 I915_WRITE(intel_dp->output_reg, intel_dp->DP);
2606 POSTING_READ(intel_dp->output_reg);
2607}
2608
2609static void intel_enable_dp(struct intel_encoder *encoder)
2610{
2611 struct intel_dp *intel_dp = enc_to_intel_dp(&encoder->base);
2612 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->base.dev;
2613 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
2614 struct intel_crtc *crtc = to_intel_crtc(encoder->base.crtc);
2615 uint32_t dp_reg = I915_READ(intel_dp->output_reg);
2616
2617 if (WARN_ON(dp_reg & DP_PORT_EN))
2618 return;
2619
2620 pps_lock(intel_dp);
2621
2622 if (IS_VALLEYVIEW(dev))
2623 vlv_init_panel_power_sequencer(intel_dp);
2624
2625 intel_dp_enable_port(intel_dp);
2626
2627 edp_panel_vdd_on(intel_dp);
2628 edp_panel_on(intel_dp);
2629 edp_panel_vdd_off(intel_dp, true);
2630
2631 pps_unlock(intel_dp);
2632
2633 if (IS_VALLEYVIEW(dev)) {
2634 unsigned int lane_mask = 0x0;
2635
2636 if (IS_CHERRYVIEW(dev))
2637 lane_mask = intel_dp_unused_lane_mask(crtc->config->lane_count);
2638
2639 vlv_wait_port_ready(dev_priv, dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp),
2640 lane_mask);
2641 }
2642
2643 intel_dp_sink_dpms(intel_dp, DRM_MODE_DPMS_ON);
2644 intel_dp_start_link_train(intel_dp);
2645 intel_dp_stop_link_train(intel_dp);
2646
2647 if (crtc->config->has_audio) {
2648 DRM_DEBUG_DRIVER("Enabling DP audio on pipe %c\n",
2649 pipe_name(crtc->pipe));
2650 intel_audio_codec_enable(encoder);
2651 }
2652}
