2683
2684static void vlv_detach_power_sequencer(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
2685{
2686 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
2687 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = intel_dig_port->base.base.dev->dev_private;
2688 enum i915_pipe pipe = intel_dp->pps_pipe;
2689 int pp_on_reg = VLV_PIPE_PP_ON_DELAYS(pipe);
2690
2691 edp_panel_vdd_off_sync(intel_dp);
2692
2693 /*
2694 * VLV seems to get confused when multiple power seqeuencers
2695 * have the same port selected (even if only one has power/vdd
2696 * enabled). The failure manifests as vlv_wait_port_ready() failing
2697 * CHV on the other hand doesn't seem to mind having the same port
2698 * selected in multiple power seqeuencers, but let's clear the
2699 * port select always when logically disconnecting a power sequencer
2700 * from a port.
2701 */
2702 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("detaching pipe %c power sequencer from port %c\n",
2703 pipe_name(pipe), port_name(intel_dig_port->port));
2704 I915_WRITE(pp_on_reg, 0);
2705 POSTING_READ(pp_on_reg);
2706
2707 intel_dp->pps_pipe = INVALID_PIPE;
2708}
2709
2710static void vlv_steal_power_sequencer(struct drm_device *dev,
2711 enum i915_pipe pipe)
2712{
2713 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv __lockdep_used = dev->dev_private;
2714 struct intel_encoder *encoder;
2715
2716 lockdep_assert_held(&dev_priv->pps_mutex);
2717
2718 if (WARN_ON(pipe != PIPE_A && pipe != PIPE_B))
2719 return;
2720
2721 list_for_each_entry(encoder, &dev->mode_config.encoder_list,
2722 base.head) {
2723 struct intel_dp *intel_dp;
2724 enum port port;
2725
2726 if (encoder->type != INTEL_OUTPUT_EDP)
2727 continue;
2728
2729 intel_dp = enc_to_intel_dp(&encoder->base);
2730 port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp)->port;
2731
2732 if (intel_dp->pps_pipe != pipe)
2733 continue;
2734
2735 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("stealing pipe %c power sequencer from port %c\n",
2736 pipe_name(pipe), port_name(port));
2737
2738 WARN(encoder->base.crtc,
2739 "stealing pipe %c power sequencer from active eDP port %c\n",
2740 pipe_name(pipe), port_name(port));
2741
2742 /* make sure vdd is off before we steal it */
2743 vlv_detach_power_sequencer(intel_dp);
2744 }
2745}
2746
2747static void vlv_init_panel_power_sequencer(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
2748{
2749 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
2750 struct intel_encoder *encoder = &intel_dig_port->base;
2751 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->base.dev;
2752 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv __lockdep_used = dev->dev_private;
2753 struct intel_crtc *crtc = to_intel_crtc(encoder->base.crtc);
2754
2755 lockdep_assert_held(&dev_priv->pps_mutex);
2756
2757 if (!is_edp(intel_dp))
2758 return;
2759
2760 if (intel_dp->pps_pipe == crtc->pipe)
2761 return;
2762
2763 /*
2764 * If another power sequencer was being used on this
2765 * port previously make sure to turn off vdd there while
2766 * we still have control of it.
2767 */
2768 if (intel_dp->pps_pipe != INVALID_PIPE)
2769 vlv_detach_power_sequencer(intel_dp);
2770
2771 /*
2772 * We may be stealing the power
2773 * sequencer from another port.
2774 */
2775 vlv_steal_power_sequencer(dev, crtc->pipe);
2776
2777 /* now it's all ours */
2778 intel_dp->pps_pipe = crtc->pipe;
2779
2780 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("initializing pipe %c power sequencer for port %c\n",
2781 pipe_name(intel_dp->pps_pipe), port_name(intel_dig_port->port));
2782
2783 /* init power sequencer on this pipe and port */
2784 intel_dp_init_panel_power_sequencer(dev, intel_dp);
2785 intel_dp_init_panel_power_sequencer_registers(dev, intel_dp);
2786}
2787
2788static void vlv_pre_enable_dp(struct intel_encoder *encoder)
2789{
2790 struct intel_dp *intel_dp = enc_to_intel_dp(&encoder->base);
2791 struct intel_digital_port *dport = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
2792 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->base.dev;
2793 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
2794 struct intel_crtc *intel_crtc = to_intel_crtc(encoder->base.crtc);
2795 enum dpio_channel port = vlv_dport_to_channel(dport);
2796 int pipe = intel_crtc->pipe;
2797 u32 val;
2798
2799 mutex_lock(&dev_priv->sb_lock);
2800
2801 val = vlv_dpio_read(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS01_DW8(port));
2802 val = 0;
2803 if (pipe)
2804 val |= (1<<21);
2805 else
2806 val &= ~(1<<21);
2807 val |= 0x001000c4;
2808 vlv_dpio_write(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS_DW8(port), val);
2809 vlv_dpio_write(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS_DW14(port), 0x00760018);
2810 vlv_dpio_write(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS_DW23(port), 0x00400888);
2811
2812 mutex_unlock(&dev_priv->sb_lock);
2813
2814 intel_enable_dp(encoder);
2815}
2816
2817static void vlv_dp_pre_pll_enable(struct intel_encoder *encoder)
2818{
2819 struct intel_digital_port *dport = enc_to_dig_port(&encoder->base);
2820 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->base.dev;
2821 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
2822 struct intel_crtc *intel_crtc =
2823 to_intel_crtc(encoder->base.crtc);
2824 enum dpio_channel port = vlv_dport_to_channel(dport);
2825 int pipe = intel_crtc->pipe;
2826
2827 intel_dp_prepare(encoder);
2828
2829 /* Program Tx lane resets to default */
2830 mutex_lock(&dev_priv->sb_lock);
2831 vlv_dpio_write(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS_DW0(port),
2832 DPIO_PCS_TX_LANE2_RESET |
2833 DPIO_PCS_TX_LANE1_RESET);
2834 vlv_dpio_write(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS_DW1(port),
2835 DPIO_PCS_CLK_CRI_RXEB_EIOS_EN |
2836 DPIO_PCS_CLK_CRI_RXDIGFILTSG_EN |
2837 (1<<DPIO_PCS_CLK_DATAWIDTH_SHIFT) |
2838 DPIO_PCS_CLK_SOFT_RESET);
2839
2840 /* Fix up inter-pair skew failure */
2841 vlv_dpio_write(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS_DW12(port), 0x00750f00);
2842 vlv_dpio_write(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_TX_DW11(port), 0x00001500);
2843 vlv_dpio_write(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_TX_DW14(port), 0x40400000);
2844 mutex_unlock(&dev_priv->sb_lock);
2845}
2846
2847static void chv_pre_enable_dp(struct intel_encoder *encoder)
2848{
2849 struct intel_dp *intel_dp = enc_to_intel_dp(&encoder->base);
2850 struct intel_digital_port *dport = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
2851 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->base.dev;
2852 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
2853 struct intel_crtc *intel_crtc =
2854 to_intel_crtc(encoder->base.crtc);
2855 enum dpio_channel ch = vlv_dport_to_channel(dport);
2856 int pipe = intel_crtc->pipe;
2857 int data, i, stagger;
2858 u32 val;
2859
2860 mutex_lock(&dev_priv->sb_lock);
2861
2862 /* allow hardware to manage TX FIFO reset source */
2863 val = vlv_dpio_read(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS01_DW11(ch));
2864 val &= ~DPIO_LANEDESKEW_STRAP_OVRD;
2865 vlv_dpio_write(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS01_DW11(ch), val);
2866
2867 if (intel_crtc->config->lane_count > 2) {
2868 val = vlv_dpio_read(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS23_DW11(ch));
2869 val &= ~DPIO_LANEDESKEW_STRAP_OVRD;
2870 vlv_dpio_write(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS23_DW11(ch), val);
2871 }
2872
2873 /* Program Tx lane latency optimal setting*/
2874 for (i = 0; i < intel_crtc->config->lane_count; i++) {
2875 /* Set the upar bit */
2876 if (intel_crtc->config->lane_count == 1)
2877 data = 0x0;
2878 else
2879 data = (i == 1) ? 0x0 : 0x1;
2880 vlv_dpio_write(dev_priv, pipe, CHV_TX_DW14(ch, i),
2881 data << DPIO_UPAR_SHIFT);
2882 }
2883
2884 /* Data lane stagger programming */
2885 if (intel_crtc->config->port_clock > 270000)
2886 stagger = 0x18;
2887 else if (intel_crtc->config->port_clock > 135000)
2888 stagger = 0xd;
2889 else if (intel_crtc->config->port_clock > 67500)
2890 stagger = 0x7;
2891 else if (intel_crtc->config->port_clock > 33750)
2892 stagger = 0x4;
2893 else
2894 stagger = 0x2;
2895
2896 val = vlv_dpio_read(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS01_DW11(ch));
2897 val |= DPIO_TX2_STAGGER_MASK(0x1f);
2898 vlv_dpio_write(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS01_DW11(ch), val);
2899
2900 if (intel_crtc->config->lane_count > 2) {
2901 val = vlv_dpio_read(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS23_DW11(ch));
2902 val |= DPIO_TX2_STAGGER_MASK(0x1f);
2903 vlv_dpio_write(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS23_DW11(ch), val);
2904 }
2905
2906 vlv_dpio_write(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS01_DW12(ch),
2907 DPIO_LANESTAGGER_STRAP(stagger) |
2908 DPIO_LANESTAGGER_STRAP_OVRD |
2909 DPIO_TX1_STAGGER_MASK(0x1f) |
2910 DPIO_TX1_STAGGER_MULT(6) |
2911 DPIO_TX2_STAGGER_MULT(0));
2912
2913 if (intel_crtc->config->lane_count > 2) {
2914 vlv_dpio_write(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS23_DW12(ch),
2915 DPIO_LANESTAGGER_STRAP(stagger) |
2916 DPIO_LANESTAGGER_STRAP_OVRD |
2917 DPIO_TX1_STAGGER_MASK(0x1f) |
2918 DPIO_TX1_STAGGER_MULT(7) |
2919 DPIO_TX2_STAGGER_MULT(5));
2920 }
2921
2922 /* Deassert data lane reset */
2923 chv_data_lane_soft_reset(encoder, false);
2924
2925 mutex_unlock(&dev_priv->sb_lock);
2926
2927 intel_enable_dp(encoder);
2928
2929 /* Second common lane will stay alive on its own now */
2930 if (dport->release_cl2_override) {
2931 chv_phy_powergate_ch(dev_priv, DPIO_PHY0, DPIO_CH1, false);
2932 dport->release_cl2_override = false;
2933 }
2934}
2935
2936static void chv_dp_pre_pll_enable(struct intel_encoder *encoder)
2937{
2938 struct intel_digital_port *dport = enc_to_dig_port(&encoder->base);
2939 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->base.dev;
2940 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
2941 struct intel_crtc *intel_crtc =
2942 to_intel_crtc(encoder->base.crtc);
2943 enum dpio_channel ch = vlv_dport_to_channel(dport);
2944 enum i915_pipe pipe = intel_crtc->pipe;
2945 unsigned int lane_mask =
2946 intel_dp_unused_lane_mask(intel_crtc->config->lane_count);
2947 u32 val;
2948
2949 intel_dp_prepare(encoder);
2950
2951 /*
2952 * Must trick the second common lane into life.
2953 * Otherwise we can't even access the PLL.
2954 */
2955 if (ch == DPIO_CH0 && pipe == PIPE_B)
2956 dport->release_cl2_override =
2957 !chv_phy_powergate_ch(dev_priv, DPIO_PHY0, DPIO_CH1, true);
2958
2959 chv_phy_powergate_lanes(encoder, true, lane_mask);
2960
2961 mutex_lock(&dev_priv->sb_lock);
2962
2963 /* Assert data lane reset */
2964 chv_data_lane_soft_reset(encoder, true);
2965
2966 /* program left/right clock distribution */
2967 if (pipe != PIPE_B) {
2968 val = vlv_dpio_read(dev_priv, pipe, _CHV_CMN_DW5_CH0);
2969 val &= ~(CHV_BUFLEFTENA1_MASK | CHV_BUFRIGHTENA1_MASK);
2970 if (ch == DPIO_CH0)
2971 val |= CHV_BUFLEFTENA1_FORCE;
2972 if (ch == DPIO_CH1)
2973 val |= CHV_BUFRIGHTENA1_FORCE;
2974 vlv_dpio_write(dev_priv, pipe, _CHV_CMN_DW5_CH0, val);
2975 } else {
2976 val = vlv_dpio_read(dev_priv, pipe, _CHV_CMN_DW1_CH1);
2977 val &= ~(CHV_BUFLEFTENA2_MASK | CHV_BUFRIGHTENA2_MASK);
2978 if (ch == DPIO_CH0)
2979 val |= CHV_BUFLEFTENA2_FORCE;
2980 if (ch == DPIO_CH1)
2981 val |= CHV_BUFRIGHTENA2_FORCE;
2982 vlv_dpio_write(dev_priv, pipe, _CHV_CMN_DW1_CH1, val);
2983 }
2984
2985 /* program clock channel usage */
2986 val = vlv_dpio_read(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS01_DW8(ch));
2987 val |= CHV_PCS_USEDCLKCHANNEL_OVRRIDE;
2988 if (pipe != PIPE_B)
2989 val &= ~CHV_PCS_USEDCLKCHANNEL;
2990 else
2991 val |= CHV_PCS_USEDCLKCHANNEL;
2992 vlv_dpio_write(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS01_DW8(ch), val);
2993
2994 if (intel_crtc->config->lane_count > 2) {
2995 val = vlv_dpio_read(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS23_DW8(ch));
2996 val |= CHV_PCS_USEDCLKCHANNEL_OVRRIDE;
2997 if (pipe != PIPE_B)
2998 val &= ~CHV_PCS_USEDCLKCHANNEL;
2999 else
3000 val |= CHV_PCS_USEDCLKCHANNEL;
3001 vlv_dpio_write(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS23_DW8(ch), val);
3002 }
3003
3004 /*
3005 * This a a bit weird since generally CL
3006 * matches the pipe, but here we need to
3007 * pick the CL based on the port.
3008 */
3009 val = vlv_dpio_read(dev_priv, pipe, CHV_CMN_DW19(ch));
3010 if (pipe != PIPE_B)
3011 val &= ~CHV_CMN_USEDCLKCHANNEL;
3012 else
3013 val |= CHV_CMN_USEDCLKCHANNEL;
3014 vlv_dpio_write(dev_priv, pipe, CHV_CMN_DW19(ch), val);
3015
3016 mutex_unlock(&dev_priv->sb_lock);
3017}
3018
3019static void chv_dp_post_pll_disable(struct intel_encoder *encoder)
3020{
3021 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = to_i915(encoder->base.dev);
3022 enum i915_pipe pipe = to_intel_crtc(encoder->base.crtc)->pipe;
3023 u32 val;
3024
3025 mutex_lock(&dev_priv->sb_lock);
3026
3027 /* disable left/right clock distribution */
3028 if (pipe != PIPE_B) {
3029 val = vlv_dpio_read(dev_priv, pipe, _CHV_CMN_DW5_CH0);
3030 val &= ~(CHV_BUFLEFTENA1_MASK | CHV_BUFRIGHTENA1_MASK);
3031 vlv_dpio_write(dev_priv, pipe, _CHV_CMN_DW5_CH0, val);
3032 } else {
3033 val = vlv_dpio_read(dev_priv, pipe, _CHV_CMN_DW1_CH1);
3034 val &= ~(CHV_BUFLEFTENA2_MASK | CHV_BUFRIGHTENA2_MASK);
3035 vlv_dpio_write(dev_priv, pipe, _CHV_CMN_DW1_CH1, val);
3036 }
3037
3038 mutex_unlock(&dev_priv->sb_lock);
3039
3040 /*
3041 * Leave the power down bit cleared for at least one
3042 * lane so that chv_powergate_phy_ch() will power
3043 * on something when the channel is otherwise unused.
3044 * When the port is off and the override is removed
3045 * the lanes power down anyway, so otherwise it doesn't
3046 * really matter what the state of power down bits is
3047 * after this.
3048 */
3049 chv_phy_powergate_lanes(encoder, false, 0x0);
3050}
3051
3052/*
3053 * Native read with retry for link status and receiver capability reads for
3054 * cases where the sink may still be asleep.
3055 *
3056 * Sinks are *supposed* to come up within 1ms from an off state, but we're also
3057 * supposed to retry 3 times per the spec.
3058 */
3059static ssize_t
3060intel_dp_dpcd_read_wake(struct drm_dp_aux *aux, unsigned int offset,
3061 void *buffer, size_t size)
3062{
3063 ssize_t ret;
3064 int i;
3065
3066 /*
3067 * Sometime we just get the same incorrect byte repeated
3068 * over the entire buffer. Doing just one throw away read
3069 * initially seems to "solve" it.
3070 */
3071 drm_dp_dpcd_read(aux, DP_DPCD_REV, buffer, 1);
3072
3073 for (i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
3074 ret = drm_dp_dpcd_read(aux, offset, buffer, size);
3075 if (ret == size)
3076 return ret;
3077 msleep(1);
3078 }
3079
3080 return ret;
3081}
3082
3083/*
3084 * Fetch AUX CH registers 0x202 - 0x207 which contain
3085 * link status information
3086 */
3087static bool
3088intel_dp_get_link_status(struct intel_dp *intel_dp, uint8_t link_status[DP_LINK_STATUS_SIZE])
3089{
3090 return intel_dp_dpcd_read_wake(&intel_dp->aux,
3091 DP_LANE0_1_STATUS,
3092 link_status,
3093 DP_LINK_STATUS_SIZE) == DP_LINK_STATUS_SIZE;
3094}

3096/* These are source-specific values. */
3097static uint8_t
3098intel_dp_voltage_max(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
3099{
3100 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dp_to_dev(intel_dp);
3101 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
3102 enum port port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp)->port;
3103
3104 if (IS_BROXTON(dev))
3105 return DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_LEVEL_3;
3106 else if (INTEL_INFO(dev)->gen >= 9) {
3107 if (dev_priv->edp_low_vswing && port == PORT_A)
3108 return DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_LEVEL_3;
3109 return DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_LEVEL_2;
3110 } else if (IS_VALLEYVIEW(dev))
3111 return DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_LEVEL_3;
3112 else if (IS_GEN7(dev) && port == PORT_A)
3113 return DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_LEVEL_2;
3114 else if (HAS_PCH_CPT(dev) && port != PORT_A)
3115 return DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_LEVEL_3;
3116 else
3117 return DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_LEVEL_2;
3118}

3293
3294static uint32_t chv_signal_levels(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
3295{
3296 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dp_to_dev(intel_dp);
3297 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
3298 struct intel_digital_port *dport = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
3299 struct intel_crtc *intel_crtc = to_intel_crtc(dport->base.base.crtc);
3300 u32 deemph_reg_value, margin_reg_value, val;
3301 uint8_t train_set = intel_dp->train_set[0];
3302 enum dpio_channel ch = vlv_dport_to_channel(dport);
3303 enum i915_pipe pipe = intel_crtc->pipe;
3304 int i;
3305
3306 switch (train_set & DP_TRAIN_PRE_EMPHASIS_MASK) {
3307 case DP_TRAIN_PRE_EMPH_LEVEL_0:
3308 switch (train_set & DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_MASK) {
3309 case DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_LEVEL_0:
3310 deemph_reg_value = 128;
3311 margin_reg_value = 52;
3312 break;
3313 case DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_LEVEL_1:
3314 deemph_reg_value = 128;
3315 margin_reg_value = 77;
3316 break;
3317 case DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_LEVEL_2:
3318 deemph_reg_value = 128;
3319 margin_reg_value = 102;
3320 break;
3321 case DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_LEVEL_3:
3322 deemph_reg_value = 128;
3323 margin_reg_value = 154;
3324 /* FIXME extra to set for 1200 */
3325 break;
3326 default:
3327 return 0;
3328 }
3329 break;
3330 case DP_TRAIN_PRE_EMPH_LEVEL_1:
3331 switch (train_set & DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_MASK) {
3332 case DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_LEVEL_0:
3333 deemph_reg_value = 85;
3334 margin_reg_value = 78;
3335 break;
3336 case DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_LEVEL_1:
3337 deemph_reg_value = 85;
3338 margin_reg_value = 116;
3339 break;
3340 case DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_LEVEL_2:
3341 deemph_reg_value = 85;
3342 margin_reg_value = 154;
3343 break;
3344 default:
3345 return 0;
3346 }
3347 break;
3348 case DP_TRAIN_PRE_EMPH_LEVEL_2:
3349 switch (train_set & DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_MASK) {
3350 case DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_LEVEL_0:
3351 deemph_reg_value = 64;
3352 margin_reg_value = 104;
3353 break;
3354 case DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_LEVEL_1:
3355 deemph_reg_value = 64;
3356 margin_reg_value = 154;
3357 break;
3358 default:
3359 return 0;
3360 }
3361 break;
3362 case DP_TRAIN_PRE_EMPH_LEVEL_3:
3363 switch (train_set & DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_MASK) {
3364 case DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_LEVEL_0:
3365 deemph_reg_value = 43;
3366 margin_reg_value = 154;
3367 break;
3368 default:
3369 return 0;
3370 }
3371 break;
3372 default:
3373 return 0;
3374 }
3375
3376 mutex_lock(&dev_priv->sb_lock);
3377
3378 /* Clear calc init */
3379 val = vlv_dpio_read(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS01_DW10(ch));
3380 val &= ~(DPIO_PCS_SWING_CALC_TX0_TX2 | DPIO_PCS_SWING_CALC_TX1_TX3);
3381 val &= ~(DPIO_PCS_TX1DEEMP_MASK | DPIO_PCS_TX2DEEMP_MASK);
3382 val |= DPIO_PCS_TX1DEEMP_9P5 | DPIO_PCS_TX2DEEMP_9P5;
3383 vlv_dpio_write(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS01_DW10(ch), val);
3384
3385 if (intel_crtc->config->lane_count > 2) {
3386 val = vlv_dpio_read(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS23_DW10(ch));
3387 val &= ~(DPIO_PCS_SWING_CALC_TX0_TX2 | DPIO_PCS_SWING_CALC_TX1_TX3);
3388 val &= ~(DPIO_PCS_TX1DEEMP_MASK | DPIO_PCS_TX2DEEMP_MASK);
3389 val |= DPIO_PCS_TX1DEEMP_9P5 | DPIO_PCS_TX2DEEMP_9P5;
3390 vlv_dpio_write(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS23_DW10(ch), val);
3391 }
3392
3393 val = vlv_dpio_read(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS01_DW9(ch));
3394 val &= ~(DPIO_PCS_TX1MARGIN_MASK | DPIO_PCS_TX2MARGIN_MASK);
3395 val |= DPIO_PCS_TX1MARGIN_000 | DPIO_PCS_TX2MARGIN_000;
3396 vlv_dpio_write(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS01_DW9(ch), val);
3397
3398 if (intel_crtc->config->lane_count > 2) {
3399 val = vlv_dpio_read(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS23_DW9(ch));
3400 val &= ~(DPIO_PCS_TX1MARGIN_MASK | DPIO_PCS_TX2MARGIN_MASK);
3401 val |= DPIO_PCS_TX1MARGIN_000 | DPIO_PCS_TX2MARGIN_000;
3402 vlv_dpio_write(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS23_DW9(ch), val);
3403 }
3404
3405 /* Program swing deemph */
3406 for (i = 0; i < intel_crtc->config->lane_count; i++) {
3407 val = vlv_dpio_read(dev_priv, pipe, CHV_TX_DW4(ch, i));
3408 val &= ~DPIO_SWING_DEEMPH9P5_MASK;
3409 val |= deemph_reg_value << DPIO_SWING_DEEMPH9P5_SHIFT;
3410 vlv_dpio_write(dev_priv, pipe, CHV_TX_DW4(ch, i), val);
3411 }
3412
3413 /* Program swing margin */
3414 for (i = 0; i < intel_crtc->config->lane_count; i++) {
3415 val = vlv_dpio_read(dev_priv, pipe, CHV_TX_DW2(ch, i));
3416
3417 val &= ~DPIO_SWING_MARGIN000_MASK;
3418 val |= margin_reg_value << DPIO_SWING_MARGIN000_SHIFT;
3419
3420 /*
3421 * Supposedly this value shouldn't matter when unique transition
3422 * scale is disabled, but in fact it does matter. Let's just
3423 * always program the same value and hope it's OK.
3424 */
3425 val &= ~(0xff << DPIO_UNIQ_TRANS_SCALE_SHIFT);
3426 val |= 0x9a << DPIO_UNIQ_TRANS_SCALE_SHIFT;
3427
3428 vlv_dpio_write(dev_priv, pipe, CHV_TX_DW2(ch, i), val);
3429 }
3430
3431 /*
3432 * The document said it needs to set bit 27 for ch0 and bit 26
3433 * for ch1. Might be a typo in the doc.
3434 * For now, for this unique transition scale selection, set bit
3435 * 27 for ch0 and ch1.
3436 */
3437 for (i = 0; i < intel_crtc->config->lane_count; i++) {
3438 val = vlv_dpio_read(dev_priv, pipe, CHV_TX_DW3(ch, i));
3439 if (chv_need_uniq_trans_scale(train_set))
3440 val |= DPIO_TX_UNIQ_TRANS_SCALE_EN;
3441 else
3442 val &= ~DPIO_TX_UNIQ_TRANS_SCALE_EN;
3443 vlv_dpio_write(dev_priv, pipe, CHV_TX_DW3(ch, i), val);
3444 }
3445
3446 /* Start swing calculation */
3447 val = vlv_dpio_read(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS01_DW10(ch));
3448 val |= DPIO_PCS_SWING_CALC_TX0_TX2 | DPIO_PCS_SWING_CALC_TX1_TX3;
3449 vlv_dpio_write(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS01_DW10(ch), val);
3450
3451 if (intel_crtc->config->lane_count > 2) {
3452 val = vlv_dpio_read(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS23_DW10(ch));
3453 val |= DPIO_PCS_SWING_CALC_TX0_TX2 | DPIO_PCS_SWING_CALC_TX1_TX3;
3454 vlv_dpio_write(dev_priv, pipe, VLV_PCS23_DW10(ch), val);
3455 }
3456
3457 mutex_unlock(&dev_priv->sb_lock);
3458
3459 return 0;
3460}
3461
3462static void
3463intel_get_adjust_train(struct intel_dp *intel_dp,
3464 const uint8_t link_status[DP_LINK_STATUS_SIZE])
3465{
3466 uint8_t v = 0;
3467 uint8_t p = 0;
3468 int lane;
3469 uint8_t voltage_max;
3470 uint8_t preemph_max;
3471
3472 for (lane = 0; lane < intel_dp->lane_count; lane++) {
3473 uint8_t this_v = drm_dp_get_adjust_request_voltage(link_status, lane);
3474 uint8_t this_p = drm_dp_get_adjust_request_pre_emphasis(link_status, lane);
3475
3476 if (this_v > v)
3477 v = this_v;
3478 if (this_p > p)
3479 p = this_p;
3480 }
3481
3482 voltage_max = intel_dp_voltage_max(intel_dp);
3483 if (v >= voltage_max)
3484 v = voltage_max | DP_TRAIN_MAX_SWING_REACHED;
3485
3486 preemph_max = intel_dp_pre_emphasis_max(intel_dp, v);
3487 if (p >= preemph_max)
3488 p = preemph_max | DP_TRAIN_MAX_PRE_EMPHASIS_REACHED;
3489
3490 for (lane = 0; lane < 4; lane++)
3491 intel_dp->train_set[lane] = v | p;
3492}

3546 return EDP_LINK_TRAIN_400_600MV_6DB_SNB_B;
3547 case DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_LEVEL_1 | DP_TRAIN_PRE_EMPH_LEVEL_1:
3548 case DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_LEVEL_2 | DP_TRAIN_PRE_EMPH_LEVEL_1:
3549 return EDP_LINK_TRAIN_600_800MV_3_5DB_SNB_B;
3550 case DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_LEVEL_2 | DP_TRAIN_PRE_EMPH_LEVEL_0:
3551 case DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_LEVEL_3 | DP_TRAIN_PRE_EMPH_LEVEL_0:
3552 return EDP_LINK_TRAIN_800_1200MV_0DB_SNB_B;
3553 default:
3554 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Unsupported voltage swing/pre-emphasis level:"
3555 "0x%x\n", signal_levels);
3556 return EDP_LINK_TRAIN_400_600MV_0DB_SNB_B;
3557 }
3558}
3559
3560/* Gen7's DP voltage swing and pre-emphasis control */
3561static uint32_t
3562gen7_edp_signal_levels(uint8_t train_set)
3563{
3564 int signal_levels = train_set & (DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_MASK |
3565 DP_TRAIN_PRE_EMPHASIS_MASK);
3566 switch (signal_levels) {
3567 case DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_LEVEL_0 | DP_TRAIN_PRE_EMPH_LEVEL_0:
3568 return EDP_LINK_TRAIN_400MV_0DB_IVB;
3569 case DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_LEVEL_0 | DP_TRAIN_PRE_EMPH_LEVEL_1:
3570 return EDP_LINK_TRAIN_400MV_3_5DB_IVB;
3571 case DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_LEVEL_0 | DP_TRAIN_PRE_EMPH_LEVEL_2:
3572 return EDP_LINK_TRAIN_400MV_6DB_IVB;
3573
3574 case DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_LEVEL_1 | DP_TRAIN_PRE_EMPH_LEVEL_0:
3575 return EDP_LINK_TRAIN_600MV_0DB_IVB;
3576 case DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_LEVEL_1 | DP_TRAIN_PRE_EMPH_LEVEL_1:
3577 return EDP_LINK_TRAIN_600MV_3_5DB_IVB;
3578
3579 case DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_LEVEL_2 | DP_TRAIN_PRE_EMPH_LEVEL_0:
3580 return EDP_LINK_TRAIN_800MV_0DB_IVB;
3581 case DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_LEVEL_2 | DP_TRAIN_PRE_EMPH_LEVEL_1:
3582 return EDP_LINK_TRAIN_800MV_3_5DB_IVB;
3583
3584 default:
3585 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Unsupported voltage swing/pre-emphasis level:"
3586 "0x%x\n", signal_levels);
3587 return EDP_LINK_TRAIN_500MV_0DB_IVB;
3588 }
3589}
3590
3591/* Properly updates "DP" with the correct signal levels. */
3592static void
3593intel_dp_set_signal_levels(struct intel_dp *intel_dp, uint32_t *DP)
3594{
3595 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
3596 enum port port = intel_dig_port->port;
3597 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dig_port->base.base.dev;
3598 uint32_t signal_levels, mask = 0;
3599 uint8_t train_set = intel_dp->train_set[0];
3600
3601 if (HAS_DDI(dev)) {
3602 signal_levels = ddi_signal_levels(intel_dp);
3603
3604 if (IS_BROXTON(dev))
3605 signal_levels = 0;
3606 else
3607 mask = DDI_BUF_EMP_MASK;
3608 } else if (IS_CHERRYVIEW(dev)) {
3609 signal_levels = chv_signal_levels(intel_dp);
3610 } else if (IS_VALLEYVIEW(dev)) {
3611 signal_levels = vlv_signal_levels(intel_dp);
3612 } else if (IS_GEN7(dev) && port == PORT_A) {
3613 signal_levels = gen7_edp_signal_levels(train_set);
3614 mask = EDP_LINK_TRAIN_VOL_EMP_MASK_IVB;
3615 } else if (IS_GEN6(dev) && port == PORT_A) {
3616 signal_levels = gen6_edp_signal_levels(train_set);
3617 mask = EDP_LINK_TRAIN_VOL_EMP_MASK_SNB;
3618 } else {
3619 signal_levels = gen4_signal_levels(train_set);
3620 mask = DP_VOLTAGE_MASK | DP_PRE_EMPHASIS_MASK;
3621 }
3622
3623 if (mask)
3624 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Using signal levels %08x\n", signal_levels);
3625
3626 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Using vswing level %d\n",
3627 train_set & DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_MASK);
3628 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Using pre-emphasis level %d\n",
3629 (train_set & DP_TRAIN_PRE_EMPHASIS_MASK) >>
3630 DP_TRAIN_PRE_EMPHASIS_SHIFT);
3631
3632 *DP = (*DP & ~mask) | signal_levels;
3633}
3634
3635static bool
3636intel_dp_set_link_train(struct intel_dp *intel_dp,
3637 uint32_t *DP,
3638 uint8_t dp_train_pat)
3639{
3640 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
3641 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv =
3642 to_i915(intel_dig_port->base.base.dev);
3643 uint8_t buf[sizeof(intel_dp->train_set) + 1];
3644 int ret, len;
3645
3646 _intel_dp_set_link_train(intel_dp, DP, dp_train_pat);
3647
3648 I915_WRITE(intel_dp->output_reg, *DP);
3649 POSTING_READ(intel_dp->output_reg);
3650
3651 buf[0] = dp_train_pat;
3652 if ((dp_train_pat & DP_TRAINING_PATTERN_MASK) ==
3653 DP_TRAINING_PATTERN_DISABLE) {
3654 /* don't write DP_TRAINING_LANEx_SET on disable */
3655 len = 1;
3656 } else {
3657 /* DP_TRAINING_LANEx_SET follow DP_TRAINING_PATTERN_SET */
3658 memcpy(buf + 1, intel_dp->train_set, intel_dp->lane_count);
3659 len = intel_dp->lane_count + 1;
3660 }
3661
3662 ret = drm_dp_dpcd_write(&intel_dp->aux, DP_TRAINING_PATTERN_SET,
3663 buf, len);
3664
3665 return ret == len;
3666}
3667
3668static bool
3669intel_dp_reset_link_train(struct intel_dp *intel_dp, uint32_t *DP,
3670 uint8_t dp_train_pat)
3671{
3672 memset(intel_dp->train_set, 0, sizeof(intel_dp->train_set));
3673 intel_dp_set_signal_levels(intel_dp, DP);
3674 return intel_dp_set_link_train(intel_dp, DP, dp_train_pat);
3675}
3676
3677static bool
3678intel_dp_update_link_train(struct intel_dp *intel_dp, uint32_t *DP,
3679 const uint8_t link_status[DP_LINK_STATUS_SIZE])
3680{
3681 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
3682 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv =
3683 to_i915(intel_dig_port->base.base.dev);
3684 int ret;
3685
3686 intel_get_adjust_train(intel_dp, link_status);
3687 intel_dp_set_signal_levels(intel_dp, DP);
3688
3689 I915_WRITE(intel_dp->output_reg, *DP);
3690 POSTING_READ(intel_dp->output_reg);
3691
3692 ret = drm_dp_dpcd_write(&intel_dp->aux, DP_TRAINING_LANE0_SET,
3693 intel_dp->train_set, intel_dp->lane_count);
3694
3695 return ret == intel_dp->lane_count;
3696}
3697
3698static void intel_dp_set_idle_link_train(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
3699{
3700 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
3701 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dig_port->base.base.dev;
3702 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
3703 enum port port = intel_dig_port->port;
3704 uint32_t val;
3705
3706 if (!HAS_DDI(dev))
3707 return;
3708
3709 val = I915_READ(DP_TP_CTL(port));
3710 val &= ~DP_TP_CTL_LINK_TRAIN_MASK;
3711 val |= DP_TP_CTL_LINK_TRAIN_IDLE;
3712 I915_WRITE(DP_TP_CTL(port), val);
3713
3714 /*
3715 * On PORT_A we can have only eDP in SST mode. There the only reason
3716 * we need to set idle transmission mode is to work around a HW issue
3717 * where we enable the pipe while not in idle link-training mode.
3718 * In this case there is requirement to wait for a minimum number of
3719 * idle patterns to be sent.
3720 */
3721 if (port == PORT_A)
3722 return;
3723
3724 if (wait_for((I915_READ(DP_TP_STATUS(port)) & DP_TP_STATUS_IDLE_DONE),
3725 1))
3726 DRM_ERROR("Timed out waiting for DP idle patterns\n");
3727}
3728
3729/* Enable corresponding port and start training pattern 1 */
3730static void
3731intel_dp_link_training_clock_recovery(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
3732{
3733 struct drm_encoder *encoder = &dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp)->base.base;
3734 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->dev;
3735 int i;
3736 uint8_t voltage;
3737 int voltage_tries, loop_tries;
3738 uint32_t DP = intel_dp->DP;
3739 uint8_t link_config[2];
3740 uint8_t link_bw, rate_select;
3741
3742 if (HAS_DDI(dev))
3743 intel_ddi_prepare_link_retrain(encoder);
3744
3745 intel_dp_compute_rate(intel_dp, intel_dp->link_rate,
3746 &link_bw, &rate_select);
3747
3748 /* Write the link configuration data */
3749 link_config[0] = link_bw;
3750 link_config[1] = intel_dp->lane_count;
3751 if (drm_dp_enhanced_frame_cap(intel_dp->dpcd))
3752 link_config[1] |= DP_LANE_COUNT_ENHANCED_FRAME_EN;
3753 drm_dp_dpcd_write(&intel_dp->aux, DP_LINK_BW_SET, link_config, 2);
3754 if (intel_dp->num_sink_rates)
3755 drm_dp_dpcd_write(&intel_dp->aux, DP_LINK_RATE_SET,
3756 &rate_select, 1);
3757
3758 link_config[0] = 0;
3759 link_config[1] = DP_SET_ANSI_8B10B;
3760 drm_dp_dpcd_write(&intel_dp->aux, DP_DOWNSPREAD_CTRL, link_config, 2);
3761
3762 DP |= DP_PORT_EN;
3763
3764 /* clock recovery */
3765 if (!intel_dp_reset_link_train(intel_dp, &DP,
3766 DP_TRAINING_PATTERN_1 |
3767 DP_LINK_SCRAMBLING_DISABLE)) {
3768 DRM_ERROR("failed to enable link training\n");
3769 return;
3770 }
3771
3772 voltage = 0xff;
3773 voltage_tries = 0;
3774 loop_tries = 0;
3775 for (;;) {
3776 uint8_t link_status[DP_LINK_STATUS_SIZE];
3777
3778 drm_dp_link_train_clock_recovery_delay(intel_dp->dpcd);
3779 if (!intel_dp_get_link_status(intel_dp, link_status)) {
3780 DRM_ERROR("failed to get link status\n");
3781 break;
3782 }
3783
3784 if (drm_dp_clock_recovery_ok(link_status, intel_dp->lane_count)) {
3785 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("clock recovery OK\n");
3786 break;
3787 }
3788
3789
3790 /* Check to see if we've tried the max voltage */
3791 for (i = 0; i < intel_dp->lane_count; i++)
3792 if ((intel_dp->train_set[i] & DP_TRAIN_MAX_SWING_REACHED) == 0)
3793 break;
3794 if (i == intel_dp->lane_count) {
3795 ++loop_tries;
3796 if (loop_tries == 5) {
3797 DRM_ERROR("too many full retries, give up\n");
3798 break;
3799 }
3800 intel_dp_reset_link_train(intel_dp, &DP,
3801 DP_TRAINING_PATTERN_1 |
3802 DP_LINK_SCRAMBLING_DISABLE);
3803 voltage_tries = 0;
3804 continue;
3805 }
3806
3807 /* Check to see if we've tried the same voltage 5 times */
3808 if ((intel_dp->train_set[0] & DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_MASK) == voltage) {
3809 ++voltage_tries;
3810 if (voltage_tries == 5) {
3811 DRM_ERROR("too many voltage retries, give up\n");
3812 break;
3813 }
3814 } else
3815 voltage_tries = 0;
3816 voltage = intel_dp->train_set[0] & DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_MASK;
3817
3818 /* Update training set as requested by target */
3819 if (!intel_dp_update_link_train(intel_dp, &DP, link_status)) {
3820 DRM_ERROR("failed to update link training\n");
3821 break;
3822 }
3823 }
3824
3825 intel_dp->DP = DP;
3826}
3827
3828static void
3829intel_dp_link_training_channel_equalization(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
3830{
3831 struct intel_digital_port *dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
3832 struct drm_device *dev = dig_port->base.base.dev;
3833 bool channel_eq = false;
3834 int tries, cr_tries;
3835 uint32_t DP = intel_dp->DP;
3836 uint32_t training_pattern = DP_TRAINING_PATTERN_2;
3837
3838 /*
3839 * Training Pattern 3 for HBR2 or 1.2 devices that support it.
3840 *
3841 * Intel platforms that support HBR2 also support TPS3. TPS3 support is
3842 * also mandatory for downstream devices that support HBR2.
3843 *
3844 * Due to WaDisableHBR2 SKL < B0 is the only exception where TPS3 is
3845 * supported but still not enabled.
3846 */
3847 if (intel_dp_source_supports_hbr2(dev) &&
3848 drm_dp_tps3_supported(intel_dp->dpcd))
3849 training_pattern = DP_TRAINING_PATTERN_3;
3850 else if (intel_dp->link_rate == 540000)
3851 DRM_ERROR("5.4 Gbps link rate without HBR2/TPS3 support\n");
3852
3853 /* channel equalization */
3854 if (!intel_dp_set_link_train(intel_dp, &DP,
3855 training_pattern |
3856 DP_LINK_SCRAMBLING_DISABLE)) {
3857 DRM_ERROR("failed to start channel equalization\n");
3858 return;
3859 }
3860
3861 tries = 0;
3862 cr_tries = 0;
3863 channel_eq = false;
3864 for (;;) {
3865 uint8_t link_status[DP_LINK_STATUS_SIZE];
3866
3867 if (cr_tries > 5) {
3868 DRM_ERROR("failed to train DP, aborting\n");
3869 break;
3870 }
3871
3872 drm_dp_link_train_channel_eq_delay(intel_dp->dpcd);
3873 if (!intel_dp_get_link_status(intel_dp, link_status)) {
3874 DRM_ERROR("failed to get link status\n");
3875 break;
3876 }
3877
3878 /* Make sure clock is still ok */
3879 if (!drm_dp_clock_recovery_ok(link_status,
3880 intel_dp->lane_count)) {
3881 intel_dp_link_training_clock_recovery(intel_dp);
3882 intel_dp_set_link_train(intel_dp, &DP,
3883 training_pattern |
3884 DP_LINK_SCRAMBLING_DISABLE);
3885 cr_tries++;
3886 continue;
3887 }
3888
3889 if (drm_dp_channel_eq_ok(link_status,
3890 intel_dp->lane_count)) {
3891 channel_eq = true;
3892 break;
3893 }
3894
3895 /* Try 5 times, then try clock recovery if that fails */
3896 if (tries > 5) {
3897 intel_dp_link_training_clock_recovery(intel_dp);
3898 intel_dp_set_link_train(intel_dp, &DP,
3899 training_pattern |
3900 DP_LINK_SCRAMBLING_DISABLE);
3901 tries = 0;
3902 cr_tries++;
3903 continue;
3904 }
3905
3906 /* Update training set as requested by target */
3907 if (!intel_dp_update_link_train(intel_dp, &DP, link_status)) {
3908 DRM_ERROR("failed to update link training\n");
3909 break;
3910 }
3911 ++tries;
3912 }
3913
3914 intel_dp_set_idle_link_train(intel_dp);
3915
3916 intel_dp->DP = DP;
3917
3918 if (channel_eq)
3919 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Channel EQ done. DP Training successful\n");
3920}
3921
3922void intel_dp_stop_link_train(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
3923{
3924 intel_dp_set_link_train(intel_dp, &intel_dp->DP,
3925 DP_TRAINING_PATTERN_DISABLE);
3926}

3928void
3929intel_dp_start_link_train(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
3930{
3931 intel_dp_link_training_clock_recovery(intel_dp);
3932 intel_dp_link_training_channel_equalization(intel_dp);
3933}
3934
3935static void
3936intel_dp_link_down(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
3937{
3938 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
3939 struct intel_crtc *crtc = to_intel_crtc(intel_dig_port->base.base.crtc);
3940 enum port port = intel_dig_port->port;
3941 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dig_port->base.base.dev;
3942 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
3943 uint32_t DP = intel_dp->DP;
3944
3945 if (WARN_ON(HAS_DDI(dev)))
3946 return;
3947
3948 if (WARN_ON((I915_READ(intel_dp->output_reg) & DP_PORT_EN) == 0))
3949 return;
3950
3951 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("\n");
3952
3953 if ((IS_GEN7(dev) && port == PORT_A) ||
3954 (HAS_PCH_CPT(dev) && port != PORT_A)) {
3955 DP &= ~DP_LINK_TRAIN_MASK_CPT;
3956 DP |= DP_LINK_TRAIN_PAT_IDLE_CPT;
3957 } else {
3958 if (IS_CHERRYVIEW(dev))
3959 DP &= ~DP_LINK_TRAIN_MASK_CHV;
3960 else
3961 DP &= ~DP_LINK_TRAIN_MASK;
3962 DP |= DP_LINK_TRAIN_PAT_IDLE;
3963 }
3964 I915_WRITE(intel_dp->output_reg, DP);
3965 POSTING_READ(intel_dp->output_reg);
3966
3967 DP &= ~(DP_PORT_EN | DP_AUDIO_OUTPUT_ENABLE);
3968 I915_WRITE(intel_dp->output_reg, DP);
3969 POSTING_READ(intel_dp->output_reg);
3970
3971 /*
3972 * HW workaround for IBX, we need to move the port
3973 * to transcoder A after disabling it to allow the
3974 * matching HDMI port to be enabled on transcoder A.
3975 */
3976 if (HAS_PCH_IBX(dev) && crtc->pipe == PIPE_B && port != PORT_A) {
3977 /* always enable with pattern 1 (as per spec) */
3978 DP &= ~(DP_PIPEB_SELECT | DP_LINK_TRAIN_MASK);
3979 DP |= DP_PORT_EN | DP_LINK_TRAIN_PAT_1;
3980 I915_WRITE(intel_dp->output_reg, DP);
3981 POSTING_READ(intel_dp->output_reg);
3982
3983 DP &= ~DP_PORT_EN;
3984 I915_WRITE(intel_dp->output_reg, DP);
3985 POSTING_READ(intel_dp->output_reg);
3986 }
3987
3988 msleep(intel_dp->panel_power_down_delay);
3989}
3990
3991static bool
3992intel_dp_get_dpcd(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
3993{
3994 struct intel_digital_port *dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
3995 struct drm_device *dev = dig_port->base.base.dev;
3996 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
3997 uint8_t rev;
3998
3999 if (intel_dp_dpcd_read_wake(&intel_dp->aux, 0x000, intel_dp->dpcd,
4000 sizeof(intel_dp->dpcd)) < 0)
4001 return false; /* aux transfer failed */
4002
4003 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("DPCD: %*ph\n", (int) sizeof(intel_dp->dpcd), intel_dp->dpcd);
4004
4005 if (intel_dp->dpcd[DP_DPCD_REV] == 0)
4006 return false; /* DPCD not present */
4007
4008 /* Check if the panel supports PSR */
4009 memset(intel_dp->psr_dpcd, 0, sizeof(intel_dp->psr_dpcd));
4010 if (is_edp(intel_dp)) {
4011 intel_dp_dpcd_read_wake(&intel_dp->aux, DP_PSR_SUPPORT,
4012 intel_dp->psr_dpcd,
4013 sizeof(intel_dp->psr_dpcd));
4014 if (intel_dp->psr_dpcd[0] & DP_PSR_IS_SUPPORTED) {
4015 dev_priv->psr.sink_support = true;
4016 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Detected EDP PSR Panel.\n");
4017 }
4018
4019 if (INTEL_INFO(dev)->gen >= 9 &&
4020 (intel_dp->psr_dpcd[0] & DP_PSR2_IS_SUPPORTED)) {
4021 uint8_t frame_sync_cap;
4022
4023 dev_priv->psr.sink_support = true;
4024 intel_dp_dpcd_read_wake(&intel_dp->aux,
4025 DP_SINK_DEVICE_AUX_FRAME_SYNC_CAP,
4026 &frame_sync_cap, 1);
4027 dev_priv->psr.aux_frame_sync = frame_sync_cap ? true : false;
4028 /* PSR2 needs frame sync as well */
4029 dev_priv->psr.psr2_support = dev_priv->psr.aux_frame_sync;
4030 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("PSR2 %s on sink",
4031 dev_priv->psr.psr2_support ? "supported" : "not supported");
4032 }
4033 }
4034
4035 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Display Port TPS3 support: source %s, sink %s\n",
4036 yesno(intel_dp_source_supports_hbr2(dev)),
4037 yesno(drm_dp_tps3_supported(intel_dp->dpcd)));
4038
4039 /* Intermediate frequency support */
4040 if (is_edp(intel_dp) &&
4041 (intel_dp->dpcd[DP_EDP_CONFIGURATION_CAP] & DP_DPCD_DISPLAY_CONTROL_CAPABLE) &&
4042 (intel_dp_dpcd_read_wake(&intel_dp->aux, DP_EDP_DPCD_REV, &rev, 1) == 1) &&
4043 (rev >= 0x03)) { /* eDp v1.4 or higher */
4044 __le16 sink_rates[DP_MAX_SUPPORTED_RATES];
4045 int i;
4046
4047 intel_dp_dpcd_read_wake(&intel_dp->aux,
4048 DP_SUPPORTED_LINK_RATES,
4049 sink_rates,
4050 sizeof(sink_rates));
4051
4052 for (i = 0; i < ARRAY_SIZE(sink_rates); i++) {
4053 int val = le16_to_cpu(sink_rates[i]);
4054
4055 if (val == 0)
4056 break;
4057
4058 /* Value read is in kHz while drm clock is saved in deca-kHz */
4059 intel_dp->sink_rates[i] = (val * 200) / 10;
4060 }
4061 intel_dp->num_sink_rates = i;
4062 }
4063
4064 intel_dp_print_rates(intel_dp);
4065
4066 if (!(intel_dp->dpcd[DP_DOWNSTREAMPORT_PRESENT] &
4067 DP_DWN_STRM_PORT_PRESENT))
4068 return true; /* native DP sink */
4069
4070 if (intel_dp->dpcd[DP_DPCD_REV] == 0x10)
4071 return true; /* no per-port downstream info */
4072
4073 if (intel_dp_dpcd_read_wake(&intel_dp->aux, DP_DOWNSTREAM_PORT_0,
4074 intel_dp->downstream_ports,
4075 DP_MAX_DOWNSTREAM_PORTS) < 0)
4076 return false; /* downstream port status fetch failed */
4077
4078 return true;
4079}

4081static void
4082intel_dp_probe_oui(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
4083{
4084 u8 buf[3];
4085
4086 if (!(intel_dp->dpcd[DP_DOWN_STREAM_PORT_COUNT] & DP_OUI_SUPPORT))
4087 return;
4088
4089 if (intel_dp_dpcd_read_wake(&intel_dp->aux, DP_SINK_OUI, buf, 3) == 3)
4090 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Sink OUI: %02hhx%02hhx%02hhx\n",
4091 buf[0], buf[1], buf[2]);
4092
4093 if (intel_dp_dpcd_read_wake(&intel_dp->aux, DP_BRANCH_OUI, buf, 3) == 3)
4094 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Branch OUI: %02hhx%02hhx%02hhx\n",
4095 buf[0], buf[1], buf[2]);
4096}
4097
4098static bool
4099intel_dp_probe_mst(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
4100{
4101 u8 buf[1];
4102
4103 if (!intel_dp->can_mst)
4104 return false;
4105
4106 if (intel_dp->dpcd[DP_DPCD_REV] < 0x12)
4107 return false;
4108
4109 if (intel_dp_dpcd_read_wake(&intel_dp->aux, DP_MSTM_CAP, buf, 1)) {
4110 if (buf[0] & DP_MST_CAP) {
4111 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Sink is MST capable\n");
4112 intel_dp->is_mst = true;
4113 } else {
4114 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Sink is not MST capable\n");
4115 intel_dp->is_mst = false;
4116 }
4117 }
4118
4119 drm_dp_mst_topology_mgr_set_mst(&intel_dp->mst_mgr, intel_dp->is_mst);
4120 return intel_dp->is_mst;
4121}
4122
4123static int intel_dp_sink_crc_stop(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
4124{
4125 struct intel_digital_port *dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
4126 struct intel_crtc *intel_crtc = to_intel_crtc(dig_port->base.base.crtc);
4127 u8 buf;
4128 int ret = 0;
4129
4130 if (drm_dp_dpcd_readb(&intel_dp->aux, DP_TEST_SINK, &buf) < 0) {
4131 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Sink CRC couldn't be stopped properly\n");
4132 ret = -EIO;
4133 goto out;
4134 }
4135
4136 if (drm_dp_dpcd_writeb(&intel_dp->aux, DP_TEST_SINK,
4137 buf & ~DP_TEST_SINK_START) < 0) {
4138 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Sink CRC couldn't be stopped properly\n");
4139 ret = -EIO;
4140 goto out;
4141 }
4142
4143 intel_dp->sink_crc.started = false;
4144 out:
4145 hsw_enable_ips(intel_crtc);
4146 return ret;
4147}
4148
4149static int intel_dp_sink_crc_start(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
4150{
4151 struct intel_digital_port *dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
4152 struct intel_crtc *intel_crtc = to_intel_crtc(dig_port->base.base.crtc);
4153 u8 buf;
4154 int ret;
4155
4156 if (intel_dp->sink_crc.started) {
4157 ret = intel_dp_sink_crc_stop(intel_dp);
4158 if (ret)
4159 return ret;
4160 }
4161
4162 if (drm_dp_dpcd_readb(&intel_dp->aux, DP_TEST_SINK_MISC, &buf) < 0)
4163 return -EIO;
4164
4165 if (!(buf & DP_TEST_CRC_SUPPORTED))
4166 return -ENOTTY;
4167
4168 intel_dp->sink_crc.last_count = buf & DP_TEST_COUNT_MASK;
4169
4170 if (drm_dp_dpcd_readb(&intel_dp->aux, DP_TEST_SINK, &buf) < 0)
4171 return -EIO;
4172
4173 hsw_disable_ips(intel_crtc);
4174
4175 if (drm_dp_dpcd_writeb(&intel_dp->aux, DP_TEST_SINK,
4176 buf | DP_TEST_SINK_START) < 0) {
4177 hsw_enable_ips(intel_crtc);
4178 return -EIO;
4179 }
4180
4181 intel_dp->sink_crc.started = true;
4182 return 0;
4183}
4184
4185int intel_dp_sink_crc(struct intel_dp *intel_dp, u8 *crc)
4186{
4187 struct intel_digital_port *dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
4188 struct drm_device *dev = dig_port->base.base.dev;
4189 struct intel_crtc *intel_crtc = to_intel_crtc(dig_port->base.base.crtc);
4190 u8 buf;
4191 int count, ret;
4192 int attempts = 6;
4193 bool old_equal_new;
4194
4195 ret = intel_dp_sink_crc_start(intel_dp);
4196 if (ret)
4197 return ret;
4198
4199 do {
4200 intel_wait_for_vblank(dev, intel_crtc->pipe);
4201
4202 if (drm_dp_dpcd_readb(&intel_dp->aux,
4203 DP_TEST_SINK_MISC, &buf) < 0) {
4204 ret = -EIO;
4205 goto stop;
4206 }
4207 count = buf & DP_TEST_COUNT_MASK;
4208
4209 /*
4210 * Count might be reset during the loop. In this case
4211 * last known count needs to be reset as well.
4212 */
4213 if (count == 0)
4214 intel_dp->sink_crc.last_count = 0;
4215
4216 if (drm_dp_dpcd_read(&intel_dp->aux, DP_TEST_CRC_R_CR, crc, 6) < 0) {
4217 ret = -EIO;
4218 goto stop;
4219 }
4220
4221 old_equal_new = (count == intel_dp->sink_crc.last_count &&
4222 !memcmp(intel_dp->sink_crc.last_crc, crc,
4223 6 * sizeof(u8)));
4224
4225 } while (--attempts && (count == 0 || old_equal_new));
4226
4227 intel_dp->sink_crc.last_count = buf & DP_TEST_COUNT_MASK;
4228 memcpy(intel_dp->sink_crc.last_crc, crc, 6 * sizeof(u8));
4229
4230 if (attempts == 0) {
4231 if (old_equal_new) {
4232 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Unreliable Sink CRC counter: Current returned CRC is identical to the previous one\n");
4233 } else {
4234 DRM_ERROR("Panel is unable to calculate any CRC after 6 vblanks\n");
4235 ret = -ETIMEDOUT;
4236 goto stop;
4237 }
4238 }
4239
4240stop:
4241 intel_dp_sink_crc_stop(intel_dp);
4242 return ret;
4243}

4250 sink_irq_vector, 1) == 1;

4278
4279static uint8_t intel_dp_autotest_edid(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
4280{
4281 uint8_t test_result = DP_TEST_NAK;
4282 struct intel_connector *intel_connector = intel_dp->attached_connector;
4283 struct drm_connector *connector = &intel_connector->base;
4284
4285 if (intel_connector->detect_edid == NULL ||
4286 connector->edid_corrupt ||
4287 intel_dp->aux.i2c_defer_count > 6) {
4288 /* Check EDID read for NACKs, DEFERs and corruption
4289 * (DP CTS 1.2 Core r1.1)
4290 * 4.2.2.4 : Failed EDID read, I2C_NAK
4291 * 4.2.2.5 : Failed EDID read, I2C_DEFER
4292 * 4.2.2.6 : EDID corruption detected
4293 * Use failsafe mode for all cases
4294 */
4295 if (intel_dp->aux.i2c_nack_count > 0 ||
4296 intel_dp->aux.i2c_defer_count > 0)
4297 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("EDID read had %d NACKs, %d DEFERs\n",
4298 intel_dp->aux.i2c_nack_count,
4299 intel_dp->aux.i2c_defer_count);
4300 intel_dp->compliance_test_data = INTEL_DP_RESOLUTION_FAILSAFE;
4301 } else {
4302 struct edid *block = intel_connector->detect_edid;
4303
4304 /* We have to write the checksum
4305 * of the last block read
4306 */
4307 block += intel_connector->detect_edid->extensions;
4308
4309 if (!drm_dp_dpcd_write(&intel_dp->aux,
4310 DP_TEST_EDID_CHECKSUM,
4311 &block->checksum,
4312 1))
4313 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Failed to write EDID checksum\n");
4314
4315 test_result = DP_TEST_ACK | DP_TEST_EDID_CHECKSUM_WRITE;
4316 intel_dp->compliance_test_data = INTEL_DP_RESOLUTION_STANDARD;
4317 }
4318
4319 /* Set test active flag here so userspace doesn't interrupt things */
4320 intel_dp->compliance_test_active = 1;
4321
4322 return test_result;
4323}

4330
4331static void intel_dp_handle_test_request(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
4332{
4333 uint8_t response = DP_TEST_NAK;
4334 uint8_t rxdata = 0;
4335 int status = 0;
4336
4337 intel_dp->compliance_test_active = 0;
4338 intel_dp->compliance_test_type = 0;
4339 intel_dp->compliance_test_data = 0;
4340
4341 intel_dp->aux.i2c_nack_count = 0;
4342 intel_dp->aux.i2c_defer_count = 0;
4343
4344 status = drm_dp_dpcd_read(&intel_dp->aux, DP_TEST_REQUEST, &rxdata, 1);
4345 if (status <= 0) {
4346 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Could not read test request from sink\n");
4347 goto update_status;
4348 }
4349
4350 switch (rxdata) {
4351 case DP_TEST_LINK_TRAINING:
4352 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("LINK_TRAINING test requested\n");
4353 intel_dp->compliance_test_type = DP_TEST_LINK_TRAINING;
4354 response = intel_dp_autotest_link_training(intel_dp);
4355 break;
4356 case DP_TEST_LINK_VIDEO_PATTERN:
4357 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("TEST_PATTERN test requested\n");
4358 intel_dp->compliance_test_type = DP_TEST_LINK_VIDEO_PATTERN;
4359 response = intel_dp_autotest_video_pattern(intel_dp);
4360 break;
4361 case DP_TEST_LINK_EDID_READ:
4362 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("EDID test requested\n");
4363 intel_dp->compliance_test_type = DP_TEST_LINK_EDID_READ;
4364 response = intel_dp_autotest_edid(intel_dp);
4365 break;
4366 case DP_TEST_LINK_PHY_TEST_PATTERN:
4367 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("PHY_PATTERN test requested\n");
4368 intel_dp->compliance_test_type = DP_TEST_LINK_PHY_TEST_PATTERN;
4369 response = intel_dp_autotest_phy_pattern(intel_dp);
4370 break;
4371 default:
4372 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Invalid test request '%02x'\n", rxdata);
4373 break;
4374 }
4375
4376update_status:
4377 status = drm_dp_dpcd_write(&intel_dp->aux,
4378 DP_TEST_RESPONSE,
4379 &response, 1);
4380 if (status <= 0)
4381 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Could not write test response to sink\n");
4382}
4383
4384static int
4385intel_dp_check_mst_status(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
4386{
4387 bool bret;
4388
4389 if (intel_dp->is_mst) {
4390 u8 esi[16] = { 0 };
4391 int ret = 0;
4392 int retry;
4393 bool handled;
4394 bret = intel_dp_get_sink_irq_esi(intel_dp, esi);
4395go_again:
4396 if (bret == true) {
4397
4398 /* check link status - esi[10] = 0x200c */
4399 if (intel_dp->active_mst_links &&
4400 !drm_dp_channel_eq_ok(&esi[10], intel_dp->lane_count)) {
4401 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("channel EQ not ok, retraining\n");
4402 intel_dp_start_link_train(intel_dp);
4403 intel_dp_stop_link_train(intel_dp);
4404 }
4405
4406 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("got esi %3ph\n", esi);
4407 ret = drm_dp_mst_hpd_irq(&intel_dp->mst_mgr, esi, &handled);
4408
4409 if (handled) {
4410 for (retry = 0; retry < 3; retry++) {
4411 int wret;
4412 wret = drm_dp_dpcd_write(&intel_dp->aux,
4413 DP_SINK_COUNT_ESI+1,
4414 &esi[1], 3);
4415 if (wret == 3) {
4416 break;
4417 }
4418 }
4419
4420 bret = intel_dp_get_sink_irq_esi(intel_dp, esi);
4421 if (bret == true) {
4422 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("got esi2 %3ph\n", esi);
4423 goto go_again;
4424 }
4425 } else
4426 ret = 0;
4427
4428 return ret;
4429 } else {
4430 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
4431 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("failed to get ESI - device may have failed\n");
4432 intel_dp->is_mst = false;
4433 drm_dp_mst_topology_mgr_set_mst(&intel_dp->mst_mgr, intel_dp->is_mst);
4434 /* send a hotplug event */
4435 drm_kms_helper_hotplug_event(intel_dig_port->base.base.dev);
4436 }
4437 }
4438 return -EINVAL;
4439}
4440
4441/*
4442 * According to DP spec
4443 * 5.1.2:
4444 * 1. Read DPCD
4445 * 2. Configure link according to Receiver Capabilities
4446 * 3. Use Link Training from 2.5.3.3 and 3.5.1.3
4447 * 4. Check link status on receipt of hot-plug interrupt
4448 */
4449static void
4450intel_dp_check_link_status(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
4451{
4452 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dp_to_dev(intel_dp);
4453 struct intel_encoder *intel_encoder = &dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp)->base;
4454 u8 sink_irq_vector;
4455 u8 link_status[DP_LINK_STATUS_SIZE];
4456
4457 WARN_ON(!drm_modeset_is_locked(&dev->mode_config.connection_mutex));
4458
4459 if (!intel_encoder->base.crtc)
4460 return;
4461
4462 if (!to_intel_crtc(intel_encoder->base.crtc)->active)
4463 return;
4464
4465 /* Try to read receiver status if the link appears to be up */
4466 if (!intel_dp_get_link_status(intel_dp, link_status)) {
4467 return;
4468 }
4469
4470 /* Now read the DPCD to see if it's actually running */
4471 if (!intel_dp_get_dpcd(intel_dp)) {
4472 return;
4473 }
4474
4475 /* Try to read the source of the interrupt */
4476 if (intel_dp->dpcd[DP_DPCD_REV] >= 0x11 &&
4477 intel_dp_get_sink_irq(intel_dp, &sink_irq_vector)) {
4478 /* Clear interrupt source */
4479 drm_dp_dpcd_writeb(&intel_dp->aux,
4480 DP_DEVICE_SERVICE_IRQ_VECTOR,
4481 sink_irq_vector);
4482
4483 if (sink_irq_vector & DP_AUTOMATED_TEST_REQUEST)
4484 DRM_DEBUG_DRIVER("Test request in short pulse not handled\n");
4485 if (sink_irq_vector & (DP_CP_IRQ | DP_SINK_SPECIFIC_IRQ))
4486 DRM_DEBUG_DRIVER("CP or sink specific irq unhandled\n");
4487 }
4488
4489 if (!drm_dp_channel_eq_ok(link_status, intel_dp->lane_count)) {
4490 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("%s: channel EQ not ok, retraining\n",
4491 intel_encoder->base.name);
4492 intel_dp_start_link_train(intel_dp);
4493 intel_dp_stop_link_train(intel_dp);
4494 }
4495}
4496
4497/* XXX this is probably wrong for multiple downstream ports */
4498static enum drm_connector_status
4499intel_dp_detect_dpcd(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
4500{
4501 uint8_t *dpcd = intel_dp->dpcd;
4502 uint8_t type;
4503
4504 if (!intel_dp_get_dpcd(intel_dp))
4505 return connector_status_disconnected;
4506
4507 /* if there's no downstream port, we're done */
4508 if (!(dpcd[DP_DOWNSTREAMPORT_PRESENT] & DP_DWN_STRM_PORT_PRESENT))
4509 return connector_status_connected;
4510
4511 /* If we're HPD-aware, SINK_COUNT changes dynamically */
4512 if (intel_dp->dpcd[DP_DPCD_REV] >= 0x11 &&
4513 intel_dp->downstream_ports[0] & DP_DS_PORT_HPD) {
4514 uint8_t reg;
4515
4516 if (intel_dp_dpcd_read_wake(&intel_dp->aux, DP_SINK_COUNT,
4517 &reg, 1) < 0)
4518 return connector_status_unknown;
4519
4520 return DP_GET_SINK_COUNT(reg) ? connector_status_connected
4521 : connector_status_disconnected;
4522 }
4523
4524 /* If no HPD, poke DDC gently */
4525 if (drm_probe_ddc(&intel_dp->aux.ddc))
4526 return connector_status_connected;
4527
4528 /* Well we tried, say unknown for unreliable port types */
4529 if (intel_dp->dpcd[DP_DPCD_REV] >= 0x11) {
4530 type = intel_dp->downstream_ports[0] & DP_DS_PORT_TYPE_MASK;
4531 if (type == DP_DS_PORT_TYPE_VGA ||
4532 type == DP_DS_PORT_TYPE_NON_EDID)
4533 return connector_status_unknown;
4534 } else {
4535 type = intel_dp->dpcd[DP_DOWNSTREAMPORT_PRESENT] &
4536 DP_DWN_STRM_PORT_TYPE_MASK;
4537 if (type == DP_DWN_STRM_PORT_TYPE_ANALOG ||
4538 type == DP_DWN_STRM_PORT_TYPE_OTHER)
4539 return connector_status_unknown;
4540 }
4541
4542 /* Anything else is out of spec, warn and ignore */
4543 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Broken DP branch device, ignoring\n");
4544 return connector_status_disconnected;
4545}

4686 * intel_digital_port_connected - is the specified port connected?
4687 * @dev_priv: i915 private structure
4688 * @port: the port to test

4743intel_dp_get_edid(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
4744{
4745 struct intel_connector *intel_connector = intel_dp->attached_connector;
4746
4747 /* use cached edid if we have one */
4748 if (intel_connector->edid) {
4749 /* invalid edid */
4750 if (IS_ERR(intel_connector->edid))
4751 return NULL;
4752
4753 return drm_edid_duplicate(intel_connector->edid);
4754 } else
4755 return drm_get_edid(&intel_connector->base,
4756 &intel_dp->aux.ddc);
4757}

4759static void
4760intel_dp_set_edid(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
4761{
4762 struct intel_connector *intel_connector = intel_dp->attached_connector;
4763 struct edid *edid;
4764
4765 edid = intel_dp_get_edid(intel_dp);
4766 intel_connector->detect_edid = edid;
4767
4768 if (intel_dp->force_audio != HDMI_AUDIO_AUTO)
4769 intel_dp->has_audio = intel_dp->force_audio == HDMI_AUDIO_ON;
4770 else
4771 intel_dp->has_audio = drm_detect_monitor_audio(edid);
4772}

4775intel_dp_unset_edid(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
4776{
4777 struct intel_connector *intel_connector = intel_dp->attached_connector;
4778
4779 kfree(intel_connector->detect_edid);
4780 intel_connector->detect_edid = NULL;
4781
4782 intel_dp->has_audio = false;

4785static enum drm_connector_status
4786intel_dp_detect(struct drm_connector *connector, bool force)
4787{
4788 struct intel_dp *intel_dp = intel_attached_dp(connector);
4789 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
4790 struct intel_encoder *intel_encoder = &intel_dig_port->base;
4791 struct drm_device *dev = connector->dev;
4792 enum drm_connector_status status;
4793 enum intel_display_power_domain power_domain;
4794 bool ret;
4795 u8 sink_irq_vector;
4796
4797 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("[CONNECTOR:%d:%s]\n",
4798 connector->base.id, connector->name);
4799 intel_dp_unset_edid(intel_dp);
4800
4801 if (intel_dp->is_mst) {
4802 /* MST devices are disconnected from a monitor POV */
4803 if (intel_encoder->type != INTEL_OUTPUT_EDP)
4804 intel_encoder->type = INTEL_OUTPUT_DISPLAYPORT;
4805 return connector_status_disconnected;
4806 }
4807
4808 power_domain = intel_display_port_aux_power_domain(intel_encoder);
4809 intel_display_power_get(to_i915(dev), power_domain);
4810
4811 /* Can't disconnect eDP, but you can close the lid... */
4812 if (is_edp(intel_dp))
4813 status = edp_detect(intel_dp);
4814 else if (HAS_PCH_SPLIT(dev))
4815 status = ironlake_dp_detect(intel_dp);
4816 else
4817 status = g4x_dp_detect(intel_dp);
4818 if (status != connector_status_connected)
4819 goto out;
4820
4821 intel_dp_probe_oui(intel_dp);
4822
4823 ret = intel_dp_probe_mst(intel_dp);
4824 if (ret) {
4825 /* if we are in MST mode then this connector
4826 won't appear connected or have anything with EDID on it */
4827 if (intel_encoder->type != INTEL_OUTPUT_EDP)
4828 intel_encoder->type = INTEL_OUTPUT_DISPLAYPORT;
4829 status = connector_status_disconnected;
4830 goto out;
4831 }
4832
4833 intel_dp_set_edid(intel_dp);
4834
4835 if (intel_encoder->type != INTEL_OUTPUT_EDP)
4836 intel_encoder->type = INTEL_OUTPUT_DISPLAYPORT;
4837 status = connector_status_connected;
4838
4839 /* Try to read the source of the interrupt */
4840 if (intel_dp->dpcd[DP_DPCD_REV] >= 0x11 &&
4841 intel_dp_get_sink_irq(intel_dp, &sink_irq_vector)) {
4842 /* Clear interrupt source */
4843 drm_dp_dpcd_writeb(&intel_dp->aux,
4844 DP_DEVICE_SERVICE_IRQ_VECTOR,
4845 sink_irq_vector);
4846
4847 if (sink_irq_vector & DP_AUTOMATED_TEST_REQUEST)
4848 intel_dp_handle_test_request(intel_dp);
4849 if (sink_irq_vector & (DP_CP_IRQ | DP_SINK_SPECIFIC_IRQ))
4850 DRM_DEBUG_DRIVER("CP or sink specific irq unhandled\n");
4851 }
4852
4853out:
4854 intel_display_power_put(to_i915(dev), power_domain);
4855 return status;
4856}
4857
4858static void
4859intel_dp_force(struct drm_connector *connector)
4860{
4861 struct intel_dp *intel_dp = intel_attached_dp(connector);
4862 struct intel_encoder *intel_encoder = &dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp)->base;
4863 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = to_i915(intel_encoder->base.dev);
4864 enum intel_display_power_domain power_domain;
4865
4866 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("[CONNECTOR:%d:%s]\n",
4867 connector->base.id, connector->name);
4868 intel_dp_unset_edid(intel_dp);
4869
4870 if (connector->status != connector_status_connected)
4871 return;
4872
4873 power_domain = intel_display_port_aux_power_domain(intel_encoder);
4874 intel_display_power_get(dev_priv, power_domain);
4875
4876 intel_dp_set_edid(intel_dp);
4877
4878 intel_display_power_put(dev_priv, power_domain);
4879
4880 if (intel_encoder->type != INTEL_OUTPUT_EDP)
4881 intel_encoder->type = INTEL_OUTPUT_DISPLAYPORT;
4882}

4884static int intel_dp_get_modes(struct drm_connector *connector)
4885{
4886 struct intel_connector *intel_connector = to_intel_connector(connector);
4887 struct edid *edid;
4888
4889 edid = intel_connector->detect_edid;
4890 if (edid) {
4891 int ret = intel_connector_update_modes(connector, edid);
4892 if (ret)
4893 return ret;
4894 }
4895
4896 /* if eDP has no EDID, fall back to fixed mode */
4897 if (is_edp(intel_attached_dp(connector)) &&
4898 intel_connector->panel.fixed_mode) {
4899 struct drm_display_mode *mode;
4900
4901 mode = drm_mode_duplicate(connector->dev,
4902 intel_connector->panel.fixed_mode);
4903 if (mode) {
4904 drm_mode_probed_add(connector, mode);
4905 return 1;
4906 }
4907 }
4908
4909 return 0;
4910}

4924
4925static int
4926intel_dp_set_property(struct drm_connector *connector,
4927 struct drm_property *property,
4928 uint64_t val)
4929{
4930 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = connector->dev->dev_private;
4931 struct intel_connector *intel_connector = to_intel_connector(connector);
4932 struct intel_encoder *intel_encoder = intel_attached_encoder(connector);
4933 struct intel_dp *intel_dp = enc_to_intel_dp(&intel_encoder->base);
4934 int ret;
4935
4936 ret = drm_object_property_set_value(&connector->base, property, val);
4937 if (ret)
4938 return ret;
4939
4940 if (property == dev_priv->force_audio_property) {
4941 int i = val;
4942 bool has_audio;
4943
4944 if (i == intel_dp->force_audio)
4945 return 0;
4946
4947 intel_dp->force_audio = i;
4948
4949 if (i == HDMI_AUDIO_AUTO)
4950 has_audio = intel_dp_detect_audio(connector);
4951 else
4952 has_audio = (i == HDMI_AUDIO_ON);
4953
4954 if (has_audio == intel_dp->has_audio)
4955 return 0;
4956
4957 intel_dp->has_audio = has_audio;
4958 goto done;
4959 }
4960
4961 if (property == dev_priv->broadcast_rgb_property) {
4962 bool old_auto = intel_dp->color_range_auto;
4963 bool old_range = intel_dp->limited_color_range;
4964
4965 switch (val) {
4966 case INTEL_BROADCAST_RGB_AUTO:
4967 intel_dp->color_range_auto = true;
4968 break;
4969 case INTEL_BROADCAST_RGB_FULL:
4970 intel_dp->color_range_auto = false;
4971 intel_dp->limited_color_range = false;
4972 break;
4973 case INTEL_BROADCAST_RGB_LIMITED:
4974 intel_dp->color_range_auto = false;
4975 intel_dp->limited_color_range = true;
4976 break;
4977 default:
4978 return -EINVAL;
4979 }
4980
4981 if (old_auto == intel_dp->color_range_auto &&
4982 old_range == intel_dp->limited_color_range)
4983 return 0;
4984
4985 goto done;
4986 }
4987
4988 if (is_edp(intel_dp) &&
4989 property == connector->dev->mode_config.scaling_mode_property) {
4990 if (val == DRM_MODE_SCALE_NONE) {
4991 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("no scaling not supported\n");
4992 return -EINVAL;
4993 }
4994
4995 if (intel_connector->panel.fitting_mode == val) {
4996 /* the eDP scaling property is not changed */
4997 return 0;
4998 }
4999 intel_connector->panel.fitting_mode = val;
5000
5001 goto done;
5002 }
5003
5004 return -EINVAL;
5005
5006done:
5007 if (intel_encoder->base.crtc)
5008 intel_crtc_restore_mode(intel_encoder->base.crtc);
5009
5010 return 0;
5011}

5013static void
5014intel_dp_connector_destroy(struct drm_connector *connector)
5015{
5016 struct intel_connector *intel_connector = to_intel_connector(connector);
5017
5018 kfree(intel_connector->detect_edid);
5019
5020 if (!IS_ERR_OR_NULL(intel_connector->edid))
5021 kfree(intel_connector->edid);
5022
5023 /* Can't call is_edp() since the encoder may have been destroyed
5024 * already. */
5025 if (connector->connector_type == DRM_MODE_CONNECTOR_eDP)
5026 intel_panel_fini(&intel_connector->panel);
5027
5028 drm_connector_cleanup(connector);
5029 kfree(connector);
5030}
5031
5032void intel_dp_encoder_destroy(struct drm_encoder *encoder)
5033{
5034 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = enc_to_dig_port(encoder);
5035 struct intel_dp *intel_dp = &intel_dig_port->dp;
5036
5037 drm_dp_aux_unregister(&intel_dp->aux);
5038 intel_dp_mst_encoder_cleanup(intel_dig_port);
5039 if (is_edp(intel_dp)) {
5040 cancel_delayed_work_sync(&intel_dp->panel_vdd_work);
5041 /*
5042 * vdd might still be enabled do to the delayed vdd off.
5043 * Make sure vdd is actually turned off here.
5044 */
5045 pps_lock(intel_dp);
5046 edp_panel_vdd_off_sync(intel_dp);
5047 pps_unlock(intel_dp);
5048
5049 if (intel_dp->edp_notifier.notifier_call) {
5050 unregister_reboot_notifier(&intel_dp->edp_notifier);
5051 intel_dp->edp_notifier.notifier_call = NULL;
5052 }
5053 }
5054 drm_encoder_cleanup(encoder);
5055 kfree(intel_dig_port);
5056}

5058void intel_dp_encoder_suspend(struct intel_encoder *intel_encoder)
5059{
5060 struct intel_dp *intel_dp = enc_to_intel_dp(&intel_encoder->base);
5061
5062 if (!is_edp(intel_dp))
5063 return;
5064
5065 /*
5066 * vdd might still be enabled do to the delayed vdd off.
5067 * Make sure vdd is actually turned off here.
5068 */
5069 cancel_delayed_work_sync(&intel_dp->panel_vdd_work);
5070 pps_lock(intel_dp);
5071 edp_panel_vdd_off_sync(intel_dp);
5072 pps_unlock(intel_dp);

5074
5075static void intel_edp_panel_vdd_sanitize(struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
5076{
5077 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
5078 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dig_port->base.base.dev;
5079 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
5080 enum intel_display_power_domain power_domain;
5081
5082 lockdep_assert_held(&dev_priv->pps_mutex);
5083
5084 if (!edp_have_panel_vdd(intel_dp))
5085 return;
5086
5087 /*
5088 * The VDD bit needs a power domain reference, so if the bit is
5089 * already enabled when we boot or resume, grab this reference and
5090 * schedule a vdd off, so we don't hold on to the reference
5091 * indefinitely.
5092 */
5093 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("VDD left on by BIOS, adjusting state tracking\n");
5094 power_domain = intel_display_port_aux_power_domain(&intel_dig_port->base);
5095 intel_display_power_get(dev_priv, power_domain);
5096
5097 edp_panel_vdd_schedule_off(intel_dp);
5098}

5100void intel_dp_encoder_reset(struct drm_encoder *encoder)
5101{
5102 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = to_i915(encoder->dev);
5103 struct intel_dp *intel_dp = enc_to_intel_dp(encoder);
5104
5105 if (!HAS_DDI(dev_priv))
5106 intel_dp->DP = I915_READ(intel_dp->output_reg);
5107
5108 if (to_intel_encoder(encoder)->type != INTEL_OUTPUT_EDP)
5109 return;
5110
5111 pps_lock(intel_dp);
5112
5113 /*
5114 * Read out the current power sequencer assignment,
5115 * in case the BIOS did something with it.
5116 */
5117 if (IS_VALLEYVIEW(encoder->dev))
5118 vlv_initial_power_sequencer_setup(intel_dp);
5119
5120 intel_edp_panel_vdd_sanitize(intel_dp);
5121
5122 pps_unlock(intel_dp);
5123}

5147
5148enum irqreturn
5149intel_dp_hpd_pulse(struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port, bool long_hpd)
5150{
5151 struct intel_dp *intel_dp = &intel_dig_port->dp;
5152 struct intel_encoder *intel_encoder = &intel_dig_port->base;
5153 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dig_port->base.base.dev;
5154 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
5155 enum intel_display_power_domain power_domain;
5156 enum irqreturn ret = IRQ_NONE;
5157
5158 if (intel_dig_port->base.type != INTEL_OUTPUT_EDP &&
5159 intel_dig_port->base.type != INTEL_OUTPUT_HDMI)
5160 intel_dig_port->base.type = INTEL_OUTPUT_DISPLAYPORT;
5161
5162 if (long_hpd && intel_dig_port->base.type == INTEL_OUTPUT_EDP) {
5163 /*
5164 * vdd off can generate a long pulse on eDP which
5165 * would require vdd on to handle it, and thus we
5166 * would end up in an endless cycle of
5167 * "vdd off -> long hpd -> vdd on -> detect -> vdd off -> ..."
5168 */
5169 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("ignoring long hpd on eDP port %c\n",
5170 port_name(intel_dig_port->port));
5171 return IRQ_HANDLED;
5172 }
5173
5174 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("got hpd irq on port %c - %s\n",
5175 port_name(intel_dig_port->port),
5176 long_hpd ? "long" : "short");
5177
5178 power_domain = intel_display_port_aux_power_domain(intel_encoder);
5179 intel_display_power_get(dev_priv, power_domain);
5180
5181 if (long_hpd) {
5182 if (!intel_digital_port_connected(dev_priv, intel_dig_port))
5183 goto mst_fail;
5184
5185 if (!intel_dp_get_dpcd(intel_dp)) {
5186 goto mst_fail;
5187 }
5188
5189 intel_dp_probe_oui(intel_dp);
5190
5191 if (!intel_dp_probe_mst(intel_dp)) {
5192 drm_modeset_lock(&dev->mode_config.connection_mutex, NULL);
5193 intel_dp_check_link_status(intel_dp);
5194 drm_modeset_unlock(&dev->mode_config.connection_mutex);
5195 goto mst_fail;
5196 }
5197 } else {
5198 if (intel_dp->is_mst) {
5199 if (intel_dp_check_mst_status(intel_dp) == -EINVAL)
5200 goto mst_fail;
5201 }
5202
5203 if (!intel_dp->is_mst) {
5204 drm_modeset_lock(&dev->mode_config.connection_mutex, NULL);
5205 intel_dp_check_link_status(intel_dp);
5206 drm_modeset_unlock(&dev->mode_config.connection_mutex);
5207 }
5208 }
5209
5210 ret = IRQ_HANDLED;
5211
5212 goto put_power;
5213mst_fail:
5214 /* if we were in MST mode, and device is not there get out of MST mode */
5215 if (intel_dp->is_mst) {
5216 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("MST device may have disappeared %d vs %d\n", intel_dp->is_mst, intel_dp->mst_mgr.mst_state);
5217 intel_dp->is_mst = false;
5218 drm_dp_mst_topology_mgr_set_mst(&intel_dp->mst_mgr, intel_dp->is_mst);
5219 }
5220put_power:
5221 intel_display_power_put(dev_priv, power_domain);
5222
5223 return ret;
5224}

5226/* Return which DP Port should be selected for Transcoder DP control */
5227int
5228intel_trans_dp_port_sel(struct drm_crtc *crtc)
5229{
5230 struct drm_device *dev = crtc->dev;
5231 struct intel_encoder *intel_encoder;
5232 struct intel_dp *intel_dp;
5233
5234 for_each_encoder_on_crtc(dev, crtc, intel_encoder) {
5235 intel_dp = enc_to_intel_dp(&intel_encoder->base);
5236
5237 if (intel_encoder->type == INTEL_OUTPUT_DISPLAYPORT ||
5238 intel_encoder->type == INTEL_OUTPUT_EDP)
5239 return intel_dp->output_reg;
5240 }
5241
5242 return -1;

5244
5245/* check the VBT to see whether the eDP is on another port */
5246bool intel_dp_is_edp(struct drm_device *dev, enum port port)
5247{
5248 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
5249 union child_device_config *p_child;
5250 int i;
5251 static const short port_mapping[] = {
5252 [PORT_B] = DVO_PORT_DPB,
5253 [PORT_C] = DVO_PORT_DPC,
5254 [PORT_D] = DVO_PORT_DPD,
5255 [PORT_E] = DVO_PORT_DPE,
5256 };
5257
5258 /*
5259 * eDP not supported on g4x. so bail out early just
5260 * for a bit extra safety in case the VBT is bonkers.
5261 */
5262 if (INTEL_INFO(dev)->gen < 5)
5263 return false;
5264
5265 if (port == PORT_A)
5266 return true;
5267
5268 if (!dev_priv->vbt.child_dev_num)
5269 return false;
5270
5271 for (i = 0; i < dev_priv->vbt.child_dev_num; i++) {
5272 p_child = dev_priv->vbt.child_dev + i;
5273
5274 if (p_child->common.dvo_port == port_mapping[port] &&
5275 (p_child->common.device_type & DEVICE_TYPE_eDP_BITS) ==
5276 (DEVICE_TYPE_eDP & DEVICE_TYPE_eDP_BITS))
5277 return true;
5278 }
5279 return false;
5280}

5307
5308static void
5309intel_dp_init_panel_power_sequencer(struct drm_device *dev,
5310 struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
5311{
5312 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
5313 struct edp_power_seq cur, vbt, spec,
5314 *final = &intel_dp->pps_delays;
5315 u32 pp_on, pp_off, pp_div = 0, pp_ctl = 0;
5316 int pp_ctrl_reg, pp_on_reg, pp_off_reg, pp_div_reg = 0;
5317
5318 lockdep_assert_held(&dev_priv->pps_mutex);
5319
5320 /* already initialized? */
5321 if (final->t11_t12 != 0)
5322 return;
5323
5324 if (IS_BROXTON(dev)) {
5325 /*
5326 * TODO: BXT has 2 sets of PPS registers.
5327 * Correct Register for Broxton need to be identified
5328 * using VBT. hardcoding for now
5329 */
5330 pp_ctrl_reg = BXT_PP_CONTROL(0);
5331 pp_on_reg = BXT_PP_ON_DELAYS(0);
5332 pp_off_reg = BXT_PP_OFF_DELAYS(0);
5333 } else if (HAS_PCH_SPLIT(dev)) {
5334 pp_ctrl_reg = PCH_PP_CONTROL;
5335 pp_on_reg = PCH_PP_ON_DELAYS;
5336 pp_off_reg = PCH_PP_OFF_DELAYS;
5337 pp_div_reg = PCH_PP_DIVISOR;
5338 } else {
5339 enum i915_pipe pipe = vlv_power_sequencer_pipe(intel_dp);
5340
5341 pp_ctrl_reg = VLV_PIPE_PP_CONTROL(pipe);
5342 pp_on_reg = VLV_PIPE_PP_ON_DELAYS(pipe);
5343 pp_off_reg = VLV_PIPE_PP_OFF_DELAYS(pipe);
5344 pp_div_reg = VLV_PIPE_PP_DIVISOR(pipe);
5345 }
5346
5347 /* Workaround: Need to write PP_CONTROL with the unlock key as
5348 * the very first thing. */
5349 pp_ctl = ironlake_get_pp_control(intel_dp);
5350
5351 pp_on = I915_READ(pp_on_reg);
5352 pp_off = I915_READ(pp_off_reg);
5353 if (!IS_BROXTON(dev)) {
5354 I915_WRITE(pp_ctrl_reg, pp_ctl);
5355 pp_div = I915_READ(pp_div_reg);
5356 }
5357
5358 /* Pull timing values out of registers */
5359 cur.t1_t3 = (pp_on & PANEL_POWER_UP_DELAY_MASK) >>
5360 PANEL_POWER_UP_DELAY_SHIFT;
5361
5362 cur.t8 = (pp_on & PANEL_LIGHT_ON_DELAY_MASK) >>
5363 PANEL_LIGHT_ON_DELAY_SHIFT;
5364
5365 cur.t9 = (pp_off & PANEL_LIGHT_OFF_DELAY_MASK) >>
5366 PANEL_LIGHT_OFF_DELAY_SHIFT;
5367
5368 cur.t10 = (pp_off & PANEL_POWER_DOWN_DELAY_MASK) >>
5369 PANEL_POWER_DOWN_DELAY_SHIFT;
5370
5371 if (IS_BROXTON(dev)) {
5372 u16 tmp = (pp_ctl & BXT_POWER_CYCLE_DELAY_MASK) >>
5373 BXT_POWER_CYCLE_DELAY_SHIFT;
5374 if (tmp > 0)
5375 cur.t11_t12 = (tmp - 1) * 1000;
5376 else
5377 cur.t11_t12 = 0;
5378 } else {
5379 cur.t11_t12 = ((pp_div & PANEL_POWER_CYCLE_DELAY_MASK) >>
5380 PANEL_POWER_CYCLE_DELAY_SHIFT) * 1000;
5381 }
5382
5383 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("cur t1_t3 %d t8 %d t9 %d t10 %d t11_t12 %d\n",
5384 cur.t1_t3, cur.t8, cur.t9, cur.t10, cur.t11_t12);
5385
5386 vbt = dev_priv->vbt.edp_pps;
5387
5388 /* Upper limits from eDP 1.3 spec. Note that we use the clunky units of
5389 * our hw here, which are all in 100usec. */
5390 spec.t1_t3 = 210 * 10;
5391 spec.t8 = 50 * 10; /* no limit for t8, use t7 instead */
5392 spec.t9 = 50 * 10; /* no limit for t9, make it symmetric with t8 */
5393 spec.t10 = 500 * 10;
5394 /* This one is special and actually in units of 100ms, but zero
5395 * based in the hw (so we need to add 100 ms). But the sw vbt
5396 * table multiplies it with 1000 to make it in units of 100usec,
5397 * too. */
5398 spec.t11_t12 = (510 + 100) * 10;
5399
5400 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("vbt t1_t3 %d t8 %d t9 %d t10 %d t11_t12 %d\n",
5401 vbt.t1_t3, vbt.t8, vbt.t9, vbt.t10, vbt.t11_t12);
5402
5403 /* Use the max of the register settings and vbt. If both are
5404 * unset, fall back to the spec limits. */
5405#define assign_final(field) final->field = (max(cur.field, vbt.field) == 0 ? \
5406 spec.field : \
5407 max(cur.field, vbt.field))
5408 assign_final(t1_t3);
5409 assign_final(t8);
5410 assign_final(t9);
5411 assign_final(t10);
5412 assign_final(t11_t12);
5413#undef assign_final
5414
5415#define get_delay(field) (DIV_ROUND_UP(final->field, 10))
5416 intel_dp->panel_power_up_delay = get_delay(t1_t3);
5417 intel_dp->backlight_on_delay = get_delay(t8);
5418 intel_dp->backlight_off_delay = get_delay(t9);
5419 intel_dp->panel_power_down_delay = get_delay(t10);
5420 intel_dp->panel_power_cycle_delay = get_delay(t11_t12);
5421#undef get_delay
5422
5423 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("panel power up delay %d, power down delay %d, power cycle delay %d\n",
5424 intel_dp->panel_power_up_delay, intel_dp->panel_power_down_delay,
5425 intel_dp->panel_power_cycle_delay);
5426
5427 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("backlight on delay %d, off delay %d\n",
5428 intel_dp->backlight_on_delay, intel_dp->backlight_off_delay);
5429}
5430
5431static void
5432intel_dp_init_panel_power_sequencer_registers(struct drm_device *dev,
5433 struct intel_dp *intel_dp)
5434{
5435 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
5436 u32 pp_on, pp_off, pp_div, port_sel = 0;
5437 int div = HAS_PCH_SPLIT(dev) ? intel_pch_rawclk(dev) : intel_hrawclk(dev);
5438 int pp_on_reg, pp_off_reg, pp_div_reg = 0, pp_ctrl_reg;
5439 enum port port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp)->port;
5440 const struct edp_power_seq *seq = &intel_dp->pps_delays;
5441
5442 lockdep_assert_held(&dev_priv->pps_mutex);
5443
5444 if (IS_BROXTON(dev)) {
5445 /*
5446 * TODO: BXT has 2 sets of PPS registers.
5447 * Correct Register for Broxton need to be identified
5448 * using VBT. hardcoding for now
5449 */
5450 pp_ctrl_reg = BXT_PP_CONTROL(0);
5451 pp_on_reg = BXT_PP_ON_DELAYS(0);
5452 pp_off_reg = BXT_PP_OFF_DELAYS(0);
5453
5454 } else if (HAS_PCH_SPLIT(dev)) {
5455 pp_on_reg = PCH_PP_ON_DELAYS;
5456 pp_off_reg = PCH_PP_OFF_DELAYS;
5457 pp_div_reg = PCH_PP_DIVISOR;
5458 } else {
5459 enum i915_pipe pipe = vlv_power_sequencer_pipe(intel_dp);
5460
5461 pp_on_reg = VLV_PIPE_PP_ON_DELAYS(pipe);
5462 pp_off_reg = VLV_PIPE_PP_OFF_DELAYS(pipe);
5463 pp_div_reg = VLV_PIPE_PP_DIVISOR(pipe);
5464 }
5465
5466 /*
5467 * And finally store the new values in the power sequencer. The
5468 * backlight delays are set to 1 because we do manual waits on them. For
5469 * T8, even BSpec recommends doing it. For T9, if we don't do this,
5470 * we'll end up waiting for the backlight off delay twice: once when we
5471 * do the manual sleep, and once when we disable the panel and wait for
5472 * the PP_STATUS bit to become zero.
5473 */
5474 pp_on = (seq->t1_t3 << PANEL_POWER_UP_DELAY_SHIFT) |
5475 (1 << PANEL_LIGHT_ON_DELAY_SHIFT);
5476 pp_off = (1 << PANEL_LIGHT_OFF_DELAY_SHIFT) |
5477 (seq->t10 << PANEL_POWER_DOWN_DELAY_SHIFT);
5478 /* Compute the divisor for the pp clock, simply match the Bspec
5479 * formula. */
5480 if (IS_BROXTON(dev)) {
5481 pp_div = I915_READ(pp_ctrl_reg);
5482 pp_div &= ~BXT_POWER_CYCLE_DELAY_MASK;
5483 pp_div |= (DIV_ROUND_UP((seq->t11_t12 + 1), 1000)
5484 << BXT_POWER_CYCLE_DELAY_SHIFT);
5485 } else {
5486 pp_div = ((100 * div)/2 - 1) << PP_REFERENCE_DIVIDER_SHIFT;
5487 pp_div |= (DIV_ROUND_UP(seq->t11_t12, 1000)
5488 << PANEL_POWER_CYCLE_DELAY_SHIFT);
5489 }
5490
5491 /* Haswell doesn't have any port selection bits for the panel
5492 * power sequencer any more. */
5493 if (IS_VALLEYVIEW(dev)) {
5494 port_sel = PANEL_PORT_SELECT_VLV(port);
5495 } else if (HAS_PCH_IBX(dev) || HAS_PCH_CPT(dev)) {
5496 if (port == PORT_A)
5497 port_sel = PANEL_PORT_SELECT_DPA;
5498 else
5499 port_sel = PANEL_PORT_SELECT_DPD;
5500 }
5501
5502 pp_on |= port_sel;
5503
5504 I915_WRITE(pp_on_reg, pp_on);
5505 I915_WRITE(pp_off_reg, pp_off);
5506 if (IS_BROXTON(dev))
5507 I915_WRITE(pp_ctrl_reg, pp_div);
5508 else
5509 I915_WRITE(pp_div_reg, pp_div);
5510
5511 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("panel power sequencer register settings: PP_ON %#x, PP_OFF %#x, PP_DIV %#x\n",
5512 I915_READ(pp_on_reg),
5513 I915_READ(pp_off_reg),
5514 IS_BROXTON(dev) ?
5515 (I915_READ(pp_ctrl_reg) & BXT_POWER_CYCLE_DELAY_MASK) :
5516 I915_READ(pp_div_reg));
5517}
5518
5519/**
5520 * intel_dp_set_drrs_state - program registers for RR switch to take effect
5521 * @dev: DRM device
5522 * @refresh_rate: RR to be programmed
5523 *
5524 * This function gets called when refresh rate (RR) has to be changed from
5525 * one frequency to another. Switches can be between high and low RR
5526 * supported by the panel or to any other RR based on media playback (in
5527 * this case, RR value needs to be passed from user space).
5528 *
5529 * The caller of this function needs to take a lock on dev_priv->drrs.
5530 */
5531static void intel_dp_set_drrs_state(struct drm_device *dev, int refresh_rate)
5532{
5533 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
5534 struct intel_encoder *encoder;
5535 struct intel_digital_port *dig_port = NULL;
5536 struct intel_dp *intel_dp = dev_priv->drrs.dp;
5537 struct intel_crtc_state *config __unused = NULL;
5538 struct intel_crtc *intel_crtc __unused = NULL;
5539 enum drrs_refresh_rate_type index = DRRS_HIGH_RR;
5540
5541 if (refresh_rate <= 0) {
5542 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Refresh rate should be positive non-zero.\n");
5543 return;
5544 }
5545
5546 if (intel_dp == NULL) {
5547 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("DRRS not supported.\n");
5548 return;
5549 }
5550
5551 /*
5552 * FIXME: This needs proper synchronization with psr state for some
5553 * platforms that cannot have PSR and DRRS enabled at the same time.
5554 */
5555
5556 dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
5557 encoder = &dig_port->base;
5558 intel_crtc = to_intel_crtc(encoder->base.crtc);
5559
5560 if (!intel_crtc) {
5561 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("DRRS: intel_crtc not initialized\n");
5562 return;
5563 }
5564
5565 config = intel_crtc->config;
5566
5567 if (dev_priv->drrs.type < SEAMLESS_DRRS_SUPPORT) {
5568 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Only Seamless DRRS supported.\n");
5569 return;
5570 }
5571
5572 if (intel_dp->attached_connector->panel.downclock_mode->vrefresh ==
5573 refresh_rate)
5574 index = DRRS_LOW_RR;
5575
5576 if (index == dev_priv->drrs.refresh_rate_type) {
5577 DRM_DEBUG_KMS(
5578 "DRRS requested for previously set RR...ignoring\n");
5579 return;
5580 }
5581
5582 if (!intel_crtc->active) {
5583 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("eDP encoder disabled. CRTC not Active\n");
5584 return;
5585 }
5586
5587 if (INTEL_INFO(dev)->gen >= 8 && !IS_CHERRYVIEW(dev)) {
5588 switch (index) {
5589 case DRRS_HIGH_RR:
5590 intel_dp_set_m_n(intel_crtc, M1_N1);
5591 break;
5592 case DRRS_LOW_RR:
5593 intel_dp_set_m_n(intel_crtc, M2_N2);
5594 break;
5595 case DRRS_MAX_RR:
5596 default:
5597 DRM_ERROR("Unsupported refreshrate type\n");
5598 }
5599 } else if (INTEL_INFO(dev)->gen > 6) {
5600 u32 reg = PIPECONF(intel_crtc->config->cpu_transcoder);
5601 u32 val;
5602
5603 val = I915_READ(reg);
5604 if (index > DRRS_HIGH_RR) {
5605 if (IS_VALLEYVIEW(dev))
5606 val |= PIPECONF_EDP_RR_MODE_SWITCH_VLV;
5607 else
5608 val |= PIPECONF_EDP_RR_MODE_SWITCH;
5609 } else {
5610 if (IS_VALLEYVIEW(dev))
5611 val &= ~PIPECONF_EDP_RR_MODE_SWITCH_VLV;
5612 else
5613 val &= ~PIPECONF_EDP_RR_MODE_SWITCH;
5614 }
5615 I915_WRITE(reg, val);
5616 }
5617
5618 dev_priv->drrs.refresh_rate_type = index;
5619
5620 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("eDP Refresh Rate set to : %dHz\n", refresh_rate);
5621}
